title: Decent for the Price
text:
UPDATE: One year of wearing these glasses and they are still unscratched and in good condition. I am surprised by this because they feel flimsy and delicate and I don't use a carrying case. It should be noted, that I have come to appreciate the lightweight feel of these glasses. I have a low nasal bridge so glasses tend to annoyingly slide down my nose but these don't. These are my go to glasses if I do any activities that makes me sweat or jostle/shake around.

I have never been able to wear aviator sunglasses because they’re too big for my face. These glasses are perfect for my small but square face. I think they are flattering and pretty comfortable. Sometimes when you buy reasonably priced sunglasses the lenses can be fairly hazy even after a cleaning and this one does not have that problem. The issue I have with these sunglasses is they feel pretty flimsy. If you don’t put them in away in your purse just right they might get bent or have a nose pad break off. They are reasonably priced and I’m glad I purchased them.

title: Lightweight Tunic Sweater
text:
At the time of this review, I was 5'6", 173 pounds, 38DDD, size 12. I bought this in XL and it fit perfectly. The material is lighter weight. Many of the PattyBoutik sweaters and tops I've purchased have material or designs that camouflage lumps and bumps. This sweater is lighter, so not as camouflaging. The length goes past my buttocks and the arms are generously cut. The neckline is a moderate sized cowl. The gray in the strip is a heather gray. There is a slit on one side of the sweater to allow for buttocks of all sizes.

I am keeping this sweater. It's not as forgiving as other Patty sweaters but still really cute.

The sweater is great with leggings. If you wear jeans and a belt, you could probably see the lumps of buttons and belt buckles.

metadata.title: PattyBoutik Women Cowl Neck Asymmetrical Hem Sweater (Black X-Large)

title: Love the Color & Style but Not Flattering on Short Wasted & Busty
text: I am apple shaped, 36DDD, 170 pounds, 5’6” and I bought a size large, which fit small in the back area. The color is nice bright tangerine. The material is soft, 100% rayon, machine washable with no stretch. The dress is a faux wrap style, which means there is no slit that’ll show too much leg. The bust area is also faux wrap with a stitch in the middle to keep from revealing too much cleavage. However, it could’ve used more than one stitch because I had a gape, which showed my bra. In addition to being a faux wrap, the waistline on me was empire waist which is not flattering on a large busted, short waisted woman like me. I think this dress would look really cute on someone  more slender or less busty. It’s a really cute dress just not flattering on my body type.

title: I'm on the fence about this shirt
text:
First off, I wanted this shirt to be 5 stars all the way, I mean it just looks sooo cool! Unfortunately it's got a few issues.

I ordered a large based on other reviews to order up, wish I would have ordered a medium. Not the shirts fault at all, however, maybe it's a different brand shirt then what others received. The material is very light and breathable but it does feel kind of like "greasy" cotton. The decal itself is heat applied as opposed to screen printed so it will crack and disintegrate over time especially if you put the shirt in the dryer. Once again not the shirts fault, just not what I was expecting. Also there is a misspelling on the shirt.

I haven't decided yet if I will return the large and exchange for a medium or just return and get my money back. I really really like the design of this shirt but kinda feel like it would fall apart very quickly. Maybe I have a "Fool Hearted Memory" when it comes to ordering clothing on Amazon 😉

title: Size UP!
text: At 5'3 and typically wearing mediums, I ordered the large knowing that most non-name brand clothing online runs small. It definitely runs smaller than expected because even the large ran small and was snug. The shirt should be labeled as form fitting since it is a very tight fit in all areas. If you like your clothes flowing and loose, size up at least a size or 2. Don't expect any stretch with it though. I actually frayed a seam by trying to stretch it a bit.  The actual shirt though is very cute and has a faint camo pattern, not the dark colors one expects. Its a very cute shirt though and goes well with jeans, shorts, or a cute skirt. Dress it up or dress it down. Or do like me and wear it as a pj shirt because it doesn't fit as expected. Don't let that deter you though; a cute shirt that just needs sized up.

title: Why is there a flap on a flap?
text:
I have a kids sized head, so I as an adult will review this and then give you the kids input. This hat is purely for looks, not functionality. The hat is WARM, but that's about it. It has fleece inside and fur on the inside of the ears. As you get to looking closer, it has these wierd flaps on the flaps and it serves no purpose. Even has a button to flip them up. For what reason? It looks silly up. Serves no function down. The velcro will get dirty easily or filled with hair for the strap. It's best unstrapped. Also, the top fur part does not told down like most. It is sewn in place up top.

As far as a childs review, it is pink and warm. It didn't turn heads or be amazed by it. This will work for winter days when they need a warm hat that I don't care if it gets dirty. Overall, cute but not functional.

title: Great quality, very pretty sweatshirt for Fall
text:
This is a really nice sweatshirt. The material is a good quality and it's well designed and made.

It fits true to size but I ordered a size up because I like to wear sweaters and sweatshirts as an outer layer on top of another shirt and it fits just as I expected.

It's lightweight, but not too light because it's still really warm. This will be great for when the weather turns a little cooler which will be pretty soon now.

I like the colors, which are subdued, but the light and dark and the pattern work well together. Also, this is almost a sweater rather than a sweatshirt -- it doesn't have that fleecy feel inside like regular sweatshirts, but it's not scratchy.

Overall, this is a pretty nice shirt for the price. It's durable and washes up well without any noticeable shrinkage.

title: Great lightweight sweater and LOVE the hood
text:
This is a very nice lightweight sweater. It's very pretty and the colors match and go together nicely.

It's fairly see-through because it's not a super-tight knit so you may want to wear something underneath if it's more than you like.

It's soft, comfy, and casual. I think it's perfect for fall and spring when you don't really want a super thick sweater, but just something to keep you warm in cool-ish weather.

I typically wear a medium, but I got a large since I wanted it to be a little more roomy since I planned on wearing this over a shirt. The large fit me great and I think the medium might have been a little tighter than I would like.

The hood is really cool. I don't actually wear the hood on very much, because it's mostly for looks, but it does come in handy when the breeze picks up. I really like the hood looks with the sweater. It's like an added touch that makes it much prettier. I've gotten a lot of positive comments on how nice this sweater looks and I think it's mostly because of the "hoodie" style. It just adds something indescribable.

Overall, it's a great addition to my wardrobe and I highly recommend it. A decent value at the current $26.

title: My Dresses Look Great Now!
text:
Perfect - exactly what I was looking for. Ordered in both red and purple... going to get a couple more in different colors :) I do East Coast Swing and Lindy Hop -- my dresses are going to look great with these under them.

text:
This shirt fits me well. I especially like the sleeve length; it's not too long. It's a boxy shirt so don't expect a feminine tapering for the waist. I will wear it because of the fit; I don't like the large one chest pocket; the color scheme is good. I cannot complain about the price. Many other shirts that look like flannel, are not flannel and "imported." Actually, for the price, comparatively, it is acceptable.

title: Perfect.
text:
I wanted something pretty that would be visible, but not over the top or gaudy. This necklace is perfect!! Not so small that it will get lost in a look, but not so big as to take over everything. Classic and elegant. The garnet is between 7 and 8 mm, so it is nicely visible in the silver scrollwork. The chain is pretty and clean looking, though I don't know how it will hold up to extended wear. I added a photo to help show the real life size.
Update: This necklace was purchased to go with my wedding dress. It is 6 months to the day since I started wearing it. I have not taken it off once. I shower in it, sleep in it, and wear it all the time. It is still beautiful. Just yesterday, I noticed a very small kink in the snake chain. I may have to replace the chain soon. Considering how I wear it, that is amazing duration for a snake chain. The pendant still looks as it did the day I received it. No scratches, no dulling of the garnet, and not a speck of tarnish.

title: Larger Masks Fit Adult Males Better
text:
Review of Reusable Washable Face Mask with Adjustable Ear Loops & Nose Clip-3 Layer Mask with Built in Cotton Filter for Extra Protection- Unisex Fits Most Adults and Teens (4Pack) sold by LivingLife

The measurements listed in the product description seem to be accurate as I found these to be 8 ½ x 5 1/8 inches (22 x 13.3 cm) but please also note that the center of the mask is curved which affects the vertical (nose to chin) fit.

These masks will fit US adult males reasonably well. My head size is probably about average and these provide pretty complete coverage although I do find these masks to ride (usually up from the chin but sometimes slipping downward) when walking and/or talking. Another ¼ inch (0.6 cm) would be great.

These are listed as being 4 layers but we obviously will only see the innermost and outermost layers which are as being cotton (inner) and a polyester mesh (outer).

A great positive for adult males in the US and similar is that the masks are pretty wide. This means that the stress points where the elastic cord are closer to the ear so is more likely to lie flat or flatter against the face reducing leakage on the sides.

Mask seems to be well constructed and stitched with no loose threads.

The nose bridge seems to be wider than usual but is also thinner than usual so does not hold its shape quite as well.

The ear loops are longer than usual and the fit is adjusted by the now common rubber or nylon tube that slides along to ear loops. The elastic cord is acceptable in terms of comfort.

Something that I always do with reusable masks is to wash before wearing, just in case. I don’t want to breathe in any residual materials, dye, etc.

Listed as being three-layered with the middle layer being 100% cotton. The outer portions seem to be some sort of polyester blend but the material used is not listed.

title: Perfect sexy costume!
text:
First off, this is such a sexy/beautiful costume, I have yet to find another one that is also this cute! My 21st birthday is this October so I wanted a halloween costume themed party and fell in love with this costume! I ordered it about a month and a half early just in case I needed to send it back for sizing- good thing I did! I'll explain below.

2nd, I normally wear a womens US Medium Tshirt, size 11-13 jeans, and I'm a 36D. I originally ordered this costume in a size medium thinking to go along with my tshirt size. It came in quick shipping, and I tried it on. I mean, it did fit on my body, but it was just a little too tight for my liking. I wanted comfort for throughout my party, and I didn't love how it showed off all of my curves and flaps just a little to much. I am not "curvy" so I don't have the cute body type where a skin-tight suit is never a question. I just have love handles every 4 inches and I wasn't feeling my greatest in the medium. As previous reviews have said, and I will attest, is that this piece is advertised as "no see-through" when in fact it's a *little* see-through. Again, previous reviewers have warned about and I will attest to, the zipper can be a little tricky to get up. A trick I used was to zip it up a few inches before putting it on, and then it's easier to zip up when it's on and already zipped a few inches. Problem solved.

But I still went through the process of returning it, which I have no issue with because I've returned amazon items before. Amazon's returning process is the easiest thing I've ever dealt with. (Props to amazon!) So I went to my local UPS Store, and got my refund in a matter of a few hours. Then I proceeded to order the large. It said it was going to take about a week til delivery, it was here in 3 days. So again, I'm impressed with (and appreciate) the quick delivery. I tried on the large and I'm in LOVE! It fits so much better, comfier, doesn't suffocate my body, and accentuates my best features (though I dont have many lol). It's stretchy & pretty breathable. I just love everything about this costume. I'll detail each pro & con of the costume:

Con 1: Just fair warning, whatever t-shirt size you wear, and depending how tight you like your clothes, you might want to order a size up. The large still hugs my body but not as suffocating as the medium. The zipper came up a lot easier on the large than the medium, but I still used that few inches before putting it on method. Worked great. When I had the medium, there were plenty of stretched lines in the costume which was another reason I decided to order a size up. The large still had some lines showing but it's not anything that would ruin the look of the costume.

Con 2: The headband is pretty weighted, so I might have to use bobbi pins or something to hold it in place. (I'm just wearing it on my own hair, not a wig like some others have done.) But honestly this headband is SO cute, and I've got a solution for the weight. So is it really that much of a "con"? Don't think so.

Pro 1: this is seriously the cutest halloween costume I have ever seen. The pink fluff on the front is SO soft, and the tail is so adorable. The headband just completes the costume and I love it!

Pro 2: it was seriously fast shipping. Both times. Maybe it's just where I live vs where they're based out of (which I dont know off the top of my head) but both times the costume beat the predicted delivery dates. Fast delivery, 'nuff said.

Pro 3: If you take into consideration the reviews telling you how to choose your size, it's just an amazing costume hands down. It's not super off-sizing, which to me is a rare thing. So I was happy to find this size a better suitor for me.

Pro 4: Ladies, get yourself some gold high heels if you can wear them! The gold bottoms on the legs look FIRE with high heels. Ugh this costume is just so sexy!

Sorry for writing a NOVEL in this review, I just wanted to clearly explain sizing for future buyers, and tell them just how happy this costume makes me. Happy Halloween or whatever the occasion it is that you're wearing a costume!

Update: I wore it for my party and OMG it was comfy the entire night! The party lasted about 8 hours, and I stayed in this costume the entire time. Got so many compliments on it!

title: Super cute outfit, well made and comfortable fit.
text:
I bought this outfit for my 3 year old foster son, and I love it! I wasn't sure I would be thrilled with the shirt, and it does have some strings that you have to end up cutting off from inside the sleeves, but it's not really a big deal and the shorts and shirt together are extremely adorable. Please enjoy my pictures. The shirt material is thing enough that it is comfortable for a child in extremely hot weather. We are in Colorado where it is dry heat, and so far it has been up to almost 90 degrees and my child was comfortable in this outfit. He was also excited to be able to button it himself as the buttons and holes are accurate and easy to use. The jeans material of the shorts is nice thick material, not cheap at all. This outfit may turn out to be our Fourth of July outfit this year.

title: Great ear protection for small kids
text:
I bought these to take my son to a monster truck show, but then the world shut down and we didn't get to go. So while these haven't been tested for their intended purpose, my son has decided that they are great for blocking out the sound of the vacuum cleaner which he really doesn't like.

The earmuffs come in nice individual packaging and have their own little carrying case. They fold up really small. I was kind of surprised (and confused at first) on how small they get.

These are definitely for kids. I thought they seemed to be really tight, so tried them on myself to make sure it wasn't hurting my son. They are definitely too small for me, but didn't feel uncomfortable. I feel like they won't fit him too long, but we will have to see how long that is, I'm not sure how quickly kids heads grow? They really fit my 3 year old perfectly and he likes them. They seem to block out noise pretty well from what I could tell when I tried them on!

title: Surprisingly good
text: I purchased this with low expectations. The price was reasonable enough that I figured it was worth the gamble. I normally wear a 32DD/34D. I purchased size C on purpose.  The biggest problem I have with my implants is the gap between them.  I have a wide breast bone and cannot achieve that close cleavage look with ANY bra I have ever tried. Never ever ever. My boobs are big enough, it's just the bra never pulls them close enough horizontally to get that look. All bras mostly focus on pushing up, not so much in. So I bought this a cup smaller on purpose. I really wanted it to be tugging 'the girls' inward before I even tied the laces. Mission accomplished! This bra is amazing at getting that cleavage I always wanted.  I had no problem with the adhesive like others complain.  I was very careful to place it on clean dry skin.  I even repositioned it a couple times before I really pushed down on it from all angles to ensure a good grip. Now, I live in Phoenix, AZ so it's literally hot as heck here. I was outside for a good amount of time while wearing this.  It didn't budge.  I noticed the very edge felt like it was slightly lifting, but it never did. It stayed  put all day long. When I finally removed it that evening, there was sweat inside.  So yup, even through heat and sweat, it stayed put. I rinsed it, used just a little baby shampoo to clean it, let it air dry, and put it away.  I am hopeful it works as well the next time. I am buying another color now. It's worth it.

title: Lovely necklace!
text:
I really like my tree of life necklace, I chose the amethyst version because I love purple, and amethyst is one of my favorite crystals. The amethyst chip crystals that make up the tree leaves appear to be genuine amethyst, and are beautiful. The handmade wire design is lovely, but please pay attention to the size of the pendant, it is very large. I missed in the description that it is 2 inches big, so if that sounds too large, I would not recommend this pendant for you.

The pendant is pretty solid, and appears to be made well. The materials do not move much when stress is placed upon them with bending, so I expect this pendant to be durable. I would recommend keeping the pendant out of small children's reach though, just in case the crystal chips break off of the design. I feel that this pendant can be worn with many outfits, from casual to dressier ones, I appreciate that versatility. The 26 inch chain is a little long for me, but it's easy to put the pendant on a different chain.

I have had no problems nor found any flaws with my pendant, it is beautiful and appears solidly made, so I would recommend this item to others. I think it would make a great gift, especially since it comes with a nice little storage pouch. I received this discounted product for my honest review, but my opinions are my own and unbiased, not influenced in any way by receiving a discount. I welcome both positive and negative feedback!

title: Cute sweater, but best suited to someone with hips well under 38" for the same baggy look
text:
I love big comfy loose sweaters, it's totally been my thing this year, and I thought this top looked so cute when I saw it. Unfortunately I will not get to wear it though, as it is too small for me. At 5'3" 130lbs I checked the size chart and the length, bust, and sleeve measurements were appropriate, so I was sure it would fit, it's big and baggy anyway. Where the bottom of the sweater falls on the hips of the model looks cute, loose and comfortable. But it will just not work for women with big hips, unfortunately. I am petite, but I have big hips, so it is very tight at the bottom, making the middle kind of just bulge over the tight part. Not a cute look, and not comfortable for me to wear. I wish there was hip measurements or a width measurement listed. My hips are about 38", and when I measured the top for this review it was 19" across, so about 38" around. So if your hips/top of your buttock areas is smaller than 38", it should be fine for you. I gave this top to my boyfriend's mom who is smaller than me, and she liked it.

I thought the sweater was a bit thinner than I expected, isn't a totally bad thing since I get warm easily, and it doesn't get too cold in Southern California anyway. The material is softish and comfortable to wear, but is not "knitted" and didn't exactly look like the photo for me, as it was a little shiny or something (see my pics), kinda weird. The sleeve cuff looks a little shorter to me too, but that isn't a big deal. There is no tag in the sweater, and it appears that you can wear it either way, both sides are the same front and back. I actually like that there is no tag, as someone with very sensitive skin related to fibromyalgia, tags can be a nuisance. The shipping time was pretty good, I ordered the top on 12/28/15, and it said it would not arrive until between 1/22/16 and 3/9/16, but I got it 1/9/16.

The bottom line is this is a cute comfortable top, but the part falling on your hips is small, so it would be best suited for someone with hips well under 38" for the same baggy look. I received this item at a discount for review purposes, but this in no way changes my opinion of the product.

title: Comfortable socks with festive holiday designs. Thin padding on soles and arch area of socks.
text:
These Christmas Holiday Socks are made up of 80% Cotton, 17% Polyester, and 3% Elastane.
None of the threads were loose on the outside of the sock or the inside of the sock.

I love the bright colors, and festive designs - perfect for this upcoming holidays!
One pair of socks is green and red, with the design of a Christmas tree.
One pair is predominantly red, with a Santa picture near the top end of the sock.
One pair is multi-colored, with the words "Merry Christmas" at the top end of the sock.

I wear size 8-1/2 men's size shoes.
These socks fit well on my feet, without bunching under the arch or at the toes after I've walked in them for a few hours around the house at night.
These socks are a bit tight around my mid-calf region (I do not have muscular calves). I resolve this by lowering the socks nearer to my ankle area.
These socks do not provide as much padding on the soles of my feet as I would like while walking on our hardwood floors; but, they feel great when I am on the carpeted areas in our home.

I've worn each pair at least once nightly, in the 6 days since I received it; each has been washed and dried once. They still fit well after washing and drying.

No washing instructions were included with the product. So, I washed these socks in the same manner as I wash previous socks that I buy at the stores: I turned the socks inside out, used a mild detergent, and used the gentle cycle on the washing machine. Then, I dried the socks by hanging them on the line in our backyard (helps to prolong the life of the socks, as opposed to putting them in the dryer).

Overall, good functional socks with eye-pleasing holiday designs.

metadata.title: WXXM Christmas Holiday Socks Unisex Colorful Fancy Crazy Design Soft Novelty Crew Socks 3 Pairs

title: Waterproof; good sensitivity to apps on my mobile devices
text:
[[VIDEOID:6d1f3a71953f430c9a2d545c8c7f3d0b]] These Sumade running gloves (size = Large) are somewhat stiff in the palm region; but, I get good dexterity at the fingertips (to get car keys out of my pockets and insert it into the ignition, or to touch the dials on my car stereo, for example).

On my 12.9" and 9.7" tablets and 5" phone, I can open up apps; I can make calls using the gloves to tap numbers on the dial pad. These gloves work so much better on all my mobile devices than the other gloves I had, thanks to touchscreen design of the fabric at the tips of the thumb, index finger, and middle finger.

However, the width of the gloves at the fingertips are too wide for me to do the finer things when I am using the two smaller mobile devices.. For instance, if I am playing a card game, it's tough for me to pick a specific card I want to use with gloves on (the fingertips of the gloves often tap the adjacent cards, rather than the card I want). So, I have to remove the gloves, and use the tips of my fingertips to choose the exact card to play.

With my 12.9" tablet, I am able to play the card games and pick out the exact card just fine while using the gloves.

These gloves do not keep my fingers as warm as some of my other, more thicker gloves. Since I have been using these gloves, temperatures in my city are about 42-50 degrees at 6-6:30 am when I leave for work.

I ran water on to my glove (tips of the gloves, palm areas, and the cuff) for over 1 minute. When I removed the glove, my hand was dry. With the outside of the glove itself wet, I was still able to open up apps on my mobile devices.

note: This large-size glove is a bit long, as the tips of my hand does not go all the way to the end of the gloves. My hand measures 7-1/2 inches from the tip of my middle finger to area where the palm meets the wrist. So, I am better off with a medium size. This is not the fault of the product; I chose the wrong size.

Overall, good waterproof property and works great on my mobile devices for most of my activities.

metadata.title: SuMade Unisex Lightweight Outdoor Warm Touchscreen Waterproof Windproof Running Driving Cycling Hiking Gloves (Black, L)

title: Soft, comfortable. Not binding in cuff area. Not too thick. Not enough warmth during winter.
text:
These socks are a comfortable fit for the ladies in our family, and for me (I wear a size 8 men's sneakers).

I love the decorative patterns. The stitching looks good; but, when I turned the socks inside out, there were several socks with a couple of loose threads.

The seams at the top of the toes do not bother me, but I can feel them rubbing on my toes occasionally when I wear these socks in my sneakers. They have not caused any noticeable marks on my skin at the end of the day after wearing these socks.

The cuff regions of the sock are not binding and do not cause ridge marks at my lower legs.
So far, in just the past week, after wearing 3 pairs of socks on separate days and washing and drying them twice, the socks have stayed up on my calf regions.

These socks do not provide me the warmth that I like when walking on my cold hardwood floors in the den early in the AM (with temperatures in the mid-50s), as they are not too thick. On the other hand, my feet don't sweat as much in these socks as they do in my thicker wool socks.

As I walk on our hardwood floors, the soles of my feet don't get as good of a padding as I would like. On our carpet floors, the soles of my feet feel better (as does the bottom of my feet and lower back).
Because they are not too thick, I can easily slide into my slip-on shoes.

Materials of the socks:
--- Merino wool 53%
--- Cotton 24%
--- Polyester 16%
--- Spandex 7%

Washing instruction (printed on each paper band that encloses a pair of socks; socks themselves do not have instructions imprinted in the material):
--- Machine wash warm
-- Tumble dry with low heat
--- Do not bleach

Overall, these are decent socks (thicker than the standard socks that I buy at a large mass merchandise store; but thinner than some of my wool socks that I wear during winter time) that I would enjoy using during the Fall/Spring season.

title: Heats up fairly quickly; sizing mis-match; small pockets
text:
[[VIDEOID:3e054decb92a0d1a24b7a0308eed6167]] Short summary:
This XXL-size vest fits well, but only because I wear medium-size shirts. There is a size mis-match to this vest.
Has USB-charging cable attached to one of the two pockets.
A power bank (not included) can only have a maximum width of 3-1/4 to 3-3/8, otherwise, it will not fit into the pocket. If a power bank does not fit into the pocket, then I will need to carry it in my hands while wearing the vest.

More details:

This heated vest, with USB-charging cable attached to the left pocket, is XXL-size.
I wear medium size shirts/sweaters. This vest fits me well.
note: I have family members who wear large-size shirts/sweaters. This vest is a tight fit on them.

To use this, I:

1. Attach the USB plug (which is attached to the vest) into my own power bank.

2. Press and hold down the power button (located on front of the vest, at upper-left side) for about 3 seconds.

3. The button then lights up red.
note: once button lights up red, pressing it again will get the button a white color. pressing it a 3rd time gives it a blue color. Then, it repeats (i.e. red ---> white ---> blue)

note #2: the red option gives 70-75 degrees Celsius
the white button gives 60-65 degrees Celsius
the blue button gives 40-45 degrees Celsius

4. When I am done wearing the vest, I hold down the power button, and after about 3 seconds, it turns off.

When I select the red option, I can feel the vest becoming warm in about 3-5 minutes.

The vest has two pockets. One pocket has the attached USB charging cable.
Besides the sizing, the other issue to note is that this vest has small pockets. I measure a pocket to be 4-3/4 inches deep, and 3-3/8 inches wide. I have small-size hands, and can barely fit my entire hand inside the pocket.

I have multiple power banks, of various widths. The widest width power bank that will fit inside the pocket has a width of 3-1/4 inches.

The inside of the vest is smooth to the touch.

There is a 1-page instruction manual. It includes washing instructions: can hand-wash or machine-wash; air dry; do not "kneed or beat".

I followed the wash instructions. After it was dried, I attached my power bank, and the vest worked.

Overall, this heating vest works for me - the size fits, I have power banks that fit into the pocket, and the vest heats up as expected.

title: Works for what I need
text: I chose this adhesive bra because it seemed so similar to one I had purchased previously, but can't seem to find anymore. It fit just as I was expecting, and the adhesive is VERY sticky so it seems like it is going to last for awhile. title: You'll want to live in this dress in the heat
text: This dress is wonderful! The V neck in the front isn't super low, so going sans a bra (if you prefer) is comfortable and covered. The dress material is  very cool against your skin. In that heat we've had here lately that was very very welcome! I'm 5'5 and ordered and XL and the length is perfect. It hits right above my ankle so if I wear flip flops or sandals I'm not stepping on the front of the dress. It is cut slightly shorter in the front than in the back and I think they did that on purpose. The dress is roomy front to back and side to side. I typically order a size larger than what I think I would fit b/c I don't like the tight feeling around my chest. This dress is a perfect fit all around. It has pockets!!!! They aren't very deep, but very comfortable for a hand rest. I haven't tested out if a key or other items wold stay in there but I think small items would. The only reason I gave this dress 4 stars instead of 5 is because the seam in the front is very strange. In the stock photos you can see on some of the dresses but not others. There is a seam right up the front. Not a deal breaker but it's just very strange there would be a seam in the front and not the back? This makes the dots not line up at all. Probably just being overly picky but if you have a seam, why not put it in the back? I get there are seams on the sides, and there are pockets, but the back piece is solid and the front is the one that's cut with a seam. I don't understand. Again, not a deal breaker just something I noticed and thought very easily could have been switched to the other side. All in all you will love this dress. It's perfect for being outside in the garden, running to the store, or throwing on some jewelry and going out to a restaurant or gathering.

title: I received a total stinker...
text:
The watch I received had defects resulting from the OEM's sloppy assembly of the item & inadequate quality assurance:

- Badly misaligned hour hand (about 20 minutes off). (When minute hand is at 12, hour hand is at 20 past the hour). This isn't the usual 'subtle' sort of misalignment, but quite gross and makes it difficult to tell the time.

- Small seconds hand STOPS anytime watch is positioned with 12 O'clock down, as typically it is worn on right wrist.

Furthermore, the Fammis listing advertises it as having a Sapphire crystal, but I have my doubts. Water tends to 'bead' on a sapphire surface, and a test I've found is reliable, to check whether the crystal is sapphire involves depositing a drop of water on the watch glass. If the drop collapses and loses shape, then the glass is made from something OTHER than sapphire, such as mineral glass, or acrylic. If the drop remains a nice round 'drop', holding together, not spreading out, the crystal *might* be synthetic sapphire; but that is not definite -- the drop will stay well formed on other types of material having 'hardness' approaching that of synthetic sapphire, examples being Seiko's "Hardlex", or Invicta's "Flame Fusion", which both pass this test.

On *this* Parnis 'Portugese' watch's crystal, the drop of water quickly collapsed and spread ... ergo, IMO, sapphire NOT!

On the positive side:

- The power reserve complication works fairly well, except that the indicator range doesn't fit very well to the max/min winding states.

- the watch contains a pristine Sea-Gull ST-2505 ébauche, which has simple but very well-done decoration (perlage) -- this is by the OEM as part of standard production of this caliber.
- the watch keeps time exceptionally well for an automatic movement: I measured on a time-grapher and got +6.5 s/d, (average of 5 positions, with delta < 4 s/d) - bordering on chronometer level performance & remarkable for an unadjusted movement. Sea-Gull has publicly stated that it keeps it's best movements for it's own watches. I would tend to guess that products are to be distributed to third parties (other watch makers, Parnis shops, etc.), unless there is some special arrangement, Sea-Gull doesn't allow the attention necessary for to really fine-tune their movements. In the real world, the ébauches tend to be inconsistent and it is up to someone else, usually the retail customer, to get them cleaned up and regulated for accuracy. I think most of the movements (including ST-25xxx) found in chop-shop brands out of China or Hong Kong are likely to be considerably less accurate than this one.

Despite being neglected after being brought into this world, the ST-2505 is a relatively recent vintage calibre and has an interesting, sophisticated design, based on Sea-Gull's having studied the 'state-of-the-art' in watch-makaing, then borrowing from what they considered the best models. At least on paper the ST-25xx compares with entry-level in-house movements of top Swiss & German luxury brands. So having a watch with this movement provides some cheap thrills if you happen to be someone who gets excited about exotic miniature-mechanical systems of this kind. Note: owing to problems getting a prototype to operate with stability at originally intended hi-beat 28.8K standard, Sea-Gull engineers decided to down-rate the ST-25 to operate at 21.6K..

In summary:
My initial inclination was to return this watch - it is, as the title of my review states, a total stinker (from an assembly, manufacturing standpoint). However, since the movement turned out to have excellent accuracy, I have decided to keep it. ...+6.5 s/d is quite fabulous, and furthermore the time-keeping is stable, with scarcely any positional variation. I can probably figure out how to align the hour hand myself, and I can live with the crippled small seconds hand, which is, in the final analysis, 'small' and mostly decorative anyway. I'm keeping my fingers crossed that whatever is interfering with the motion of the small seconds hands won't eventually also cause deterioration of the accuracy of the main hour and minute hands.

While this watch has many redeeming qualities, and in this review I didn't even mention it's beautiful sunburst silver dial, ....the fact is that the watch sent to me is badly made, and I believe falsely advertises a sapphire crystal. This is a coveted feature and highlighting that it has a Sapphire crystal in the title of the item seems unlikely to be just an oversight. Amazon shoppers have directly asked Fammis if it is a Sapphire crystal, but Fammis gave no response. In my opinion purchasing this product from this seller is a very risky proposition. If my review has planted doubts in you mind, I think you are having an appropriate response! I got badly burned on this purchase, and I think odds high that the same could happen to you - so my only recommendation on this one is: BUYER BEWARE!

ON THE OTHER HAND, If you can't resist the allure of the Parnis Portuguese, and it is a very attractive piece, available for not much money. So if you are willing to take the risk, you could get lucky and get 'a good one'... clearly from reading the reviews, there are others who have been more fortunate than I was!

metadata.title: Fanmis White Dial Sapphire Seagull Movement Power Reserve Men's Portugal Style Automatic Watch

title: Lovely, stylish dress watch.
text:
Manufacturer's suggested retail price for this model is $295.00.
Nice. A few things that might not be obvious from photos:
- Watch face is 'silverish', not white, or at least it appears so in low light conditions. In brighter light it does appear to be pure white - I think from refraction of light by the weave pattern applied to the dial. The pattern consists of offset rows of tiny, raised chevrons.
- Breguet style hands have interesting, shifting color, depending on light and view angle. At times they appear metallic midnight blue (a shimmering, starling like color) and at other times pure black. They are not 'blued' by heat (as it appears in the photo) - the color effects is quite different and results from a slick paint treatment.
- Dress watch, so there is NO lume on this watch.
- Not a diver's watch, so NO screw-down crown. Screw down exhibition (see-through) case back. Watch should have excellent water resistance, indicated as 100M on case-back & in manual.
- Crystal described as "synthetic-sapphire, which is doubtful - other retail site listings indicate it's Seiko's proprietary Hardlex crystal. ... in any case slightly domed and seems to have anti-reflective treatment of some kind.
- Dial looks and watch wears a bit bigger than expected. The watch face IS big, using up most of the 42 (43?) mm diameter of the case, (as there is only a fairly narrow bezel). Easy to read time. I feel this is too large for a dress watch. Also, the wide diameter of the dial isn't well proportioned with respect to the Roman numerals. -2 stars for aesthetic bungling here.
- Case has smoothly rounded sides.

- Seiko 4R35-00P0 automatic movement, with hacking and winding. Exceptionally accurate, over a seven day test it ran 6 seconds slow (losing ~ 1 second per day). From my own experience & what I've heard from others, the 4R3x series has outstanding out-of-the-box accuracy. Seiko's engineering really shines in the current line of automatic movements.
- Bracelet clasp is a smallish fold-over type, and there is no secondary locking clasp. Lug width is 20mm.

metadata.title: Jazba - LIZARDO 1X

title: Beautiful Detailed Bracelet! Not Meant to be Loose Fitting
text:
I absolutely love this bracelet!! I usually wear much daintier bracelets so I wanted something a little chunkier that would stand out more and make a statement.. and, also to pair with my daintier bracelets. This was the perfect solution!! This bracelet is simple but has lovely details on the edges of each link that I think makes it extra pretty! Is really makes the bracelet shine and shimmer. The gold is just right and is clean and fresh looking.. there’s nothing cheap looking about this bracelet to me.

The bracelet is a perfect length for me. I have small wrists and this fits me perfectly but the snug fit is something to mention and be aware of. As shown in the product pictures, this is not meant to be a loose fitting bracelet. I got the assumption immediately that this was to be a more “form fitting” bracelet, which is what I wanted. If you have larger wrists or if you’re looking for a “baggier” fit, this is not the bracelet for you. The bracelet does have multiple spaces/links for different lengths though. I noticed other reviewers mention it is too small but I think it’s important to understand this isn’t meant to be loose and the product pictures perfectly show the actual type of fit. I suggest measuring your wrist if you are concerned about the length and/or fit. The width of the bracelet is perfect for me too.. it’s dainty for this type of link bracelet but still makes a lovely statement. And the weight is substantial but definitely not overly heavy.

As far as quality, i feel this is amazing quality! I have worn this often for several weeks since it arrived and i have had no problems with tarnishing, if this does occur i will update my review but so far its still perfect and shiny.

I think this is a gorgeous bracelet that is incredibly versatile and absolutely beautiful. The quality is well worth the price and the attention to detail is wonderful! I couldn’t be happier with mine!

metadata.title: The GLD Shop 6MM Figaro Chain Bracelet, 6"-7.5" - Gold

title: Came Missing a Stone - Caused Irritation….
text:
Since Amazon wouldn’t publish my original HONEST review that mentioned all that caused me to be unhappy with these earrings (came missing a stone, plated over BRASS, caused irritation, poor quality, not actually aquamarine as description “suggests”.. and the list goes on…) i guess, because others like the product, i’m supposed to as well..

I did not like these earrings. The hurt my ears and caused irritation after 1/2 an hour. They came missing a stone as the picture with the arrow best illustrates. They are gold plated over BRASS which is NOT hypoallergenic so naturally they cause issues to sensitive ears. They come with zero authenticity and I cannot find ANY stamp on the earrings or the earring backs.

Just because others like the earrings doesn’t mean they are 100% good earrings. I am simply trying to give an HONEST review which is what amazon asks me to do.

I do not recommend these. Mine literally came broken so naturally, I can’t and won’t be wearing them outside of testing them out for review sake. But my biggest issue is the actual quality which i feel is very poor and that the materials used cause pain and irritation.. other need and deserve to know that

I went into detail about my issues and displeasure with the earrings but my original review sat unpublished for over a week so, since I’m not able to clarify my opinion by being completely honest and detailing that honestly, i will simply say you’re taking your chances with these. The missing stone is the least of my worries, the quality is poor and basic. Others deserve to know if they’re going to spend $100 on earrings.

I personally do not recommend these. Sorry if that upsets anyone but it is my honest opinion.

title: Great Onesie & Great Price
text:
I ordered the extra large because I am plus sized. I wear a 2X in tops and 18/20 in pants.

A little bit top heavy, so I wanted to make sure I could button the buttons over my boobs.

If you are a plus sized man or woman, the XL onesie will fit you perfectly.
I do believe however, if you are 300 or more pounds it might not fit as well, or at all.
That's why I gave you my sizes.

The fit is very good.
I am 5"3 tall, so the legs of the onesie go right down to my ankles.
The ankles on the onesie are elasticized.
The legs are not as baggy as the rest of the onesie.
So it's kind of funny. it looks like you have these little stick legs, and from your hips up everything is so big and baggy..lol

You can either Unbutton it to use the bathroom, or use the zipper in the back.
I tried the zipper method. it's quick and easy, and you are given enough room, to do what you have to do.

The body part of the onesie is quite large and baggy.
The only thing I noticed is there is a little bit of gapping in between each button.

I usually wear a T-shirt or tank top underneath my onesie, so I just leave it unbuttoned on the top.

But if I wanted to wear it out as a costume, I would have to pin on the inside to eliminate the gapping.

The arms are comfortable. They were not tight or constricting.

The hood/head part is what really makes the costume cute. I absolutely love the yellow unicorn Horn, the eyes, etc. that's the part that attracts all of the attention. Also the tail is cute too LOL

If I fall asleep in it I do wake up quite warm in the middle of the night.
It seems kind of thin, but when you are under the blankets, you do remain warm.

I also love to wear it after I am home.
I am settling in for the night, I get on my computer, Blog, etc. it's perfect.

The price was 29.99 . I was looking at a few other styles on Amazon. There is one popular brand of onesies that start at $60 each.
So not only did I save 30+ dollars, I received this in two days, and everything about it is pretty much perfect and what I wanted it to be .

PS I chose the blue unicorn style

title: Wonderful band for my Apple Watch
text:
I rarely give anything five stars. If it were possible this item would get four and a half stars!!

This item is fabulous! I got a beautiful high-quality pink and blue watch band and the matching pink/rose gold watch face protector looks beautiful. It also came with a clear one which is good to use with my other watch bands.

I have used these items a few times now and they are still as clean and new looking as the day I got them the watch face protector is not chipping or scratched.

The rose gold color almost looks as if I bought the Rosegold watch face! I’ve had a few people ask me if it is the Rosegold watch. But I like sharing my secret with them. So they too can get a rose gold watch face for a fraction of the cost.

I change the watch face wallpaper and it looks as if I have the Nike sport watch with a blue and pink band.

I will definitely buy more products from this company for my Apple Watch

title: LOVE THIS HAT!!!! Comfy, soft and fuzzy! Great Quality!! Great Price!!!
text: I LOVE THIS HAT!!! So I have never owned one of these style of hats so I thought I would give it a try. I live in Northern California, and use this hat for those exceptionally cold days when I take my dog an early morning walk. I ordered this in the biggest size because I have a huge dome and I like my hats fitting me a little loose. It works very well to keep your head, ears, and cheeks  shielded from the cold and wind. The fur is so comfy and cozy I even wear this hat in the house. When I need a little more ventilation I fold the ears back to keep the neck part covered  or fold the ears up to give my ears and neck more breathing room but still have the warmth on the top of my head and top of my ears. This is the second hat ordered, I returned the first one only because I wanted it to be perfect and one ear was a tad fuzzier than the other,(thats just me being picky hehe. ) the sellers immediately shipped a replacement within a few days, it came with paid shipping envelope and I sent the first one back. Nonetheless, these hats are nice n toasty and I love it!

title: A dressier henley
text:
[[ASIN:B01HERGHQC Mrignt Mens Short Sleeve Slim Fit Henley t-shirt with Button (XXL, Black)]] I ordered this shirt for my husband. His favorite casual cut is a Henley so he has several. Why would he need another? Most of his others, frankly, look like thermal underwear. That’s what attracted me to this -- it’s a dressier version that he could wear with his khakis. The v-collar helps dress it up a bit too. The material has a nice sheen to it without being Jimmy Wah’s Shiny Green Suit.

He tried it on as soon as it arrived and was delighted. He has a 48” chest so I ordered the XXL. Shoulders were a dead-perfect fit. Waist is a little loose, which I wasn’t expecting with a slim fit, but it doesn’t billow or fold. He said it was cool and comfortable (this review written in a hot and muggy August). The buttons are purely decorative, but at this price point I don’t expect much. There are no care instructions. It’s come through a permanent press wash just fine. Husband is happy, I like how he looks in it, and we can’t argue with the price.

I disclose that I received a discount on this item for review. I am not affiliated with the seller or manufacturer.

title: Great for Shorter Rides – Just Watch the Sizing
text:
I picked up a pair of these women’s biker shorts for my wife and she’s quite happy with them. In her words:

I wanted a longer leg, higher waist, but no seat padding for shorter rides. These shorts are perfect. The fabric is soft and breathable with a jersey-like feel. (Note, the description says they are 88% polyester, but my tag says they are made from 88% nylon and 12% spandex – no polyester).

I would describe the fit as firm, but not tight with no gaps around the leg. The pockets are deep and wide enough for my Samsung phone. I normally wear a size 12, so ordered a Large. I didn’t realize this was CN large and US medium, but they fit perfectly the first time I put them on. However, be advised – if you plan to run them through the washer and dryer (which I do), you might want to order a size up, because they shrunk just a bit (not enough to prevent wearing them again). Other than the shrinkage, they came through the first wash just fine – no frayed seams, no pilling, and the same soft jersey-like feel.

title: I LOVE IT!!
text:
I was SOOOO nervous about this because the reviews were so all over the place and a lot of the 5 star ones received their dress for free. I'm SO glad I just took a chance because it's easily one of my new favorite dresses!!!

Material is very soft, flowy, and airy. The colors and patterns are beautiful!!

I usually wear a M/L (my measurements for ref - 38, 33, 41), so I bought an XL according to the size chart and this fits exactly how I wanted it to. It is not tight at all and has the perfect amount of 'looseness'. The waistband is elastic; fits like a glove around my waist with PLENTY of give. The slits come up to about mid thigh, but their positions keep them concealed so it's not like it's open for the world to see the entire time. I'm 5'4 and this just kisses the ground, a cute pair of wedges would solve that completely. Even wearing flats would work because it flows so nicely, it would not interfere with walking.

Overall, LOVE! I cannot wait to use this on vacation and during the summer!

title: I'm a Very Comfortable and Bright Box
text:
This particular color on me doesn’t do the shirt justice, however, I can attest to it being incredibly comfortable! I will say I was little disappointed when I first got the shirt because it looked like a square sack with absolutely no shape. Perhaps that’s because it seems to run large? I wear a small, which I ordered, but the shirt comes down below my hips when I stand normally and the sleeves are very roomy. The advertised mock neck was true to the listing at least, as well as the color being spot-on as to what’s shown in the pictures.

So far the quality and durability have been great. The color hasn’t faded at all after several washes now and it’s still as comfortable as it was the first day I got it. It hasn’t shrunk or stretched either so that’s a good sign.

Overall it’s an incredibly comfortable and relaxed piece, though it looks a little plain and baggy on its own (without outwear or accessories). I’m giving it 4 stars for comfort and it being accurate to the pictures, but taking off a star for it running large and having less shape than what it looked like in the pictures.

metadata.title: Womens Short Sleeve Mock Neck Soft Stretchy Ribbed Knit Loose Casual Solid Color Tee Shirt Tops

title: Summer Fashion Staple with Little Functionality
text:
Between booty shorts and grandma pants, I’ve always had trouble finding the perfect pair of shorts, but these EAEAO cargo shorts are exactly what I need. They are high-waisted without riding up my thigh/crotch area and still end around my mid-thighs (I’m 5’2).

While I wouldn’t call these cargo shorts, I enjoy them nonetheless. The material is on the thicker side and they have a stretchy waistband with an adjustable tie. There are 4 pockets: 2 in the front and 2 more on the sides (however you wouldn’t be able to fit a phone in any of these pockets since the two side pockets are partially sewn into the front pockets, cutting off half of it, and the side pockets are too short). The 2 back “pockets” are fake, only having a decorative flap, and the “one zip-closure security pocket” that is advertised is non-existent.

While the pockets are less than satisfactory, I still enjoy these shorts for summer, as they are quite roomy, easy and comfortable to walk in, and still look chic while retaining some functionality.

Overall I’d give them a 3 out of 5. I personally really like the shorts and will continue to use them, but between the pockets, misleading advertising, and the fact they’re not very functional CARGO shorts, the price you’re paying for what you’re supposed to receive isn’t that great.

metadata.title: EAEAO Women's Cargo Shorts (Black, M)

title: Your Outfit’s Missing Piece
text:
This crown is incredibly gorgeous: not only is it well made (with a welded metal back), the rhinestones and overall design look amazing.

The packaging itself is also well thought out: mine came in a black box with a magnetized flap. Inside they included black paper ribbons that the crown was on top of, as well as a couple of heavy-duty bobby pins. Immediately out of the box, I noticed that the crown’s topmost section was bent, but it was easy to bend back into place. One other flaw I saw was that the two main gemstones on the front are misaligned, but other than that, especially from a distance, these defects aren’t noticeable at all.

Like I said before, the crown’s back and base all look welded together, although the gemstones are glued into place. The crown is easy to wear, as it fits like a headband and the ends have loops where you can secure it with the included bobby pins. The color is accurate to the pictures, though in the sunlight it looks a lot lighter (and the smaller stones are a lot more visible).

It may be that a size large would do the trick and fit in a more comfortable way but I'm hesitant to try as it seems the cut is especially tight at the belly which isn't flattering unless you have washboard abs. title: Works well and is effective for cycling, other sports
text:
The Turnhier Bike Shorts are designed to be used for long cycling expeditions but can be used for other exercises.

I have now used this for cycling and for my favorite exercise, HIIT aerobics. The pants are pretty, with a heavily elasticized waist (more so than I have seen with other bike shorts). The ones for women have a pretty pink design that goes down the outside of the leg. I am 5'2", 150 pounds and normally wear a size 8 or 10 and these fit fine. I wore these for cycling around our neighborhood and other areas and they are comfortable. I do casual cycling. They worked well for that but I did not have the chance to do a very long trip. When I do I will edit this review. I can say that they work well despite the ample padding in the you-know-what area for other exercises. The HIIT workout I did was great with these on with no slippage, or discomfort noticed whatsoever.

I also thought these were a good price. I recommend these.

metadata.title: Turnhier Bike Shorts Padding for Women Comfortable Cycling Shorts, Women Biking Shorts Quick Dry

title: Goes perfect with a tankini
text:
The Ocean Blues Women's Adjustable High Waisted Bikini Bottom Tummy Control Tankini Swimsuit is perfect to match with a tankini top.

Having separate tankini pieces is all the rage now. If you are a small top but large bottom up until fairly recently it has been hard to find a swimsuit that would fit, because you had to buy the pieces together. Now that's over and I am glad, it is easier for me (and other women) to find a bathing suit that is flattering. This is easy to wear and I have matched this with most of my tankini tops. I am 5'2" and around 150 pounds and this fits me well-I am normally between a size 8 and a size 10. This fit well. This does keep your tummy in-I don't have much of one at this time but I do have a bulge. The way the top folds down hides this well. This is well made and looks like it will last a while.

I'll be using this a lot for the beach and the pool this year (we can still swim here, it is not too cold) and for years to come.

metadata.title: Ocean Blues Women's Black Supper High Waisted Shirring Bathing Suit Tummy Control Full Coverage Bikini Bottom Size Medium

title: Not for women
text:
Jeff & Aimy's Warm, Luxurious Cashmere Feel Winter Scarf for Women (blue cat design) is wonderful-if you are around five to eight years old.

The description on this reads a women's scarf, and unfortunately it is not. This is simply too small to be a woman's scarf-perhaps I could wrap it around my wrists if I get cold?-I am not sure. This is approximately half the size of what a normal size woman's scarf is. However, I love the material used. This is very soft on your skin and does feel good to wear. The design is really cute. The stitching of the cat face is very distinct, and the blue color with the white stitching accents is very pretty. I like the white ball at the end.

Overall, I wish I could wear this, alas I am way over the real life age range for this scarf. I love cats and the color blue so that is a shame. But this is great for a child in the age range I earlier described who loves cats.

metadata.title: Womens Warm Cozy Cashmere Feel Winter Scarf for Women Soft Woven Cat Scarves Solid Color Blue

title: A review of the Moyabo Women's 3/4 cuffed sleeve shirt
text:
The Moyabo Women's 3/4 cuffed sleeve shirt is an attractive shirt that is not built to last, but you will enjoy wearing before you wash it.

The pink color of this shirt is nice which is why I decided to try it and I liked the lace design around the neck. The sleeves come straight and are rolled with a strap on the shirt that attaches them. The buttons are pretty and functional. When I wore this, I wore this with leggings and high pairs of boots and received many compliments. This is a comfortable, casual shirt that was perfect for me at work on casual days.

My issue with this shirt is that once I started washing it this began to fall apart. This is a polyester blend of some sort. Buttons began to fall off. The lace began to get caught with other things in the laundry. This shirt pilled. In order for this shirt to last, perhaps you need to dry clean it? I'm not sure-I am used to blends being able to wash. This was a lot of fun to wear, but is not built to last you past a season of wearing it.

title: Beautiful
text:
I guessed the size, based on all the reviews, to go one size larger. I fall closest to the XL on the chart, so I bought XXL. Very glad I did. It’s a tad large, but looks great, not like I’m swimming in it. This has a very flattering sliming hourglass shape. Drapes nicely without too much flare.
I like the material. But was not happy with the black details on the hemline design. It’s screen printed on with some heavy thick ink stuff. I’m not sure how that will wear, if it will crack and peel off or fade out. I’ll hand wash and dry flat just in case. The olive green is fantastic so I’m keeping the shirt. The hemline is not too short in front for leggings, but I’m 5’4”. Now that I know my size, I’ll be ordering more 👍🏻

metadata.title: Laksmi Tunics for Women Short Sleeve, Printed Asymmetrical Hem Flow Top Casual Tee Shirts,OliveGreen XX-Large

title: Don’t hesitate!  Just get this...you’ll love it!
text:
This set is fantastic! YES YES, Do order these!! Do it now!!
Arrived with a slight plastic smell. I put them all in the dryer with a wet hand towel doused with fabric softener...a short fluff...and the smell was gone!
I ABSOLUTELY LOVE these cubes, they have the little clip-straps inside, that hold the items inside secure...like folded shirts, etc.
That makes such a huge difference.
I ordered two different style sets to compare them, and HANDS DOWN, this set is by far superior.
I kinda felt these cubes were small...until I started to fill them. They hold a lot! I was really amazed at the difference it made to use the cubes instead of just “loose stuff” inside a suitcase like I’ve done for 50+ years. I’m totally converted.
The cubes are easily manageable. A nice variety of sizes are provided. Zippers are sturdy, the mesh fronts let me see what’s inside. What’s not to like?!
The shoe-bag alone is a hoot! We put inside: my moccasin slippers, hubby’s slippers, a pair of (ladies) flat sandals, my spare eyeglasses in a hard case, hubbys’s extra reading glasses in a hard case, plus some other small loose items...and in the separate mesh pocket our flip-flop shower shoes and an additional pair of flip-flop style sandals for me. I’m amazed. 😁👍🏻

title: My new favorite sports bra from this brand
text:

This bra is very comfortable and fits great. The fabric feels good and the quality is great. It was very well made and it does not pinch, scratch, or anything. I love the style of this bra, but was afraid it would cause some fat bulges around my back, but it did not. I would say it's a medium impact sports bra and I would not mind going for a run in it.
I would definitely purchase it again. I have another sports bra from this brand, but by far, this is my favorite one.

title: Well Fitting, Comfortable Cap that Has an Adjustable Back Strap with Fastener
text:
Everybody who wears denim jeans and shirts needs a denim cap because they look so cool together. However, the Rebel Canyon Men's Denim Unstructured Dad Hat has more than just style going for it.

The cap is very light weight and almost feels like it's not even there when you wear it. The cap is very comfortable and it is adjustable to fit most sized heads. I especially like that, instead of using a Velcro fastener, Rebel Canyon selected an adjustable back strap with a metal fastener to adjust the size of the cap. It's more retro and that fits with the cap's style. While the Velcro is easier to use especially if several people wear the same cap, I find that the back strap with fastener to be a more reliable manner to adjust the cap size.

While wearing the cap is a walking advertisement for Rebel Canyon, who wouldn't find the idea of walking around with the word "Rebel" marked on their forehead to be something of a statement!

title: Not like the picture, not unisex, overpriced. Pass!
text:
Okay, I almost never return anything I've purchased on Amazon. And this was the first time I've ever had to. Here's what's wrong with these sunglasses.

1) The picture gives you the impression that the frames and lenses are champagne colored, with a light tint on the lenses. Not even close. The frames do have a gold/champagne like color to them, but in certain light, they also almost have a rose like tint to them. The lenses are dark brown, and only look like the pictures when direct light is passing through. In other words, they will look dark brown on your face.

2) These are small frames made for someone with a slender face or a child. You get no sense of that in the picture.

3) The item description says these are "unisex", but I disagree. These sunglasses are definitely more suitable for a woman's face. They just have a feminine look to them that is not conveyed in the pictures.

4) For $25, these are terribly overpriced. I've bought sunglasses like these at half the price, and twice the quality. The frame is a rather ordinary plastic. Not cheap, but certainly not high-end. There are no flexible hinges on the stems, and you don't even receive a nice gift box or bag, or cloth for wiping the lenses. These sunglasses should be sold for no more than $10.

title: It's good quality but the black hands on a black face ...
text:
Hey, for $27.00 this watch is ok. It's good quality but the black hands on a black face makes it difficult to tell time. And the other gadgets are pretty useless. One last gripe, nonwhere does it say where is manufactured. I know that Volga was actually another Russian company until 1956 or so. Then when the wall came down, Volga had a difficult time manufacturing watches in Russia. Even quality was bad...must've been during the drunk days of Yeltsin. So the company looked towards China to make these watches in order not to go bankrupt.

I bought this watch because I wanted the Volga brand on the face so wish granted. Any other expectations from this watch other than telling time are unrealistic. Buy it if you want a conversation piece to share.

title: It's ok.
text:
I have been looking for a sweater like this one for a while and I figured, why not? It took about a month to arrive and since I was going for more of the "slouchy" look, I went up one size. I am glad I did but also thinking if the fit would look more similar to the picture if I ordered my normal size.

Pros:
1. the material is very soft and the color I ordered (beige) was nice.

2. With me ordering an XL (I am 5' 4", 141 lbs), i did accomplish the baggy/slouchy look.

3. For the price, it really is not bad for this sweater.

Cons:

1. it did take a while to arrive (but that is understandable with it originating in China).

2. Where I lean towards the other side regarding going up a size, I am glad I did because the large would have been really tight in the shoulder area.

3. It does not fit the same in that area in the shoulders, and as a matter of fact, the look does look a little different than the picture.

I really can't recommend to order your size or go up one because it really depends on your individual shape, but, if you are looking for a really baggy look, I would say it would be safe going up just one size.

title: Many uses, well-made
text: My daughter is into survival gear and loves paracord bracelets, so getting this for her was a no-brainer. It will definitely come in handy on camping trips, with its whistle, compass and flint firestarter! It's well-made, not too heavy, and the buckle is comfortable and secure.  The whistle is nice and loud, and the flint sparks up easily and stores away securely when you aren't using it, and the metal piece can also be used for cutting. She is well-versed in the uses for paracord, so she's set! I received the bracelet at a discount in exchange for my honest review, and we're very impressed with the many uses and the quality of construction. I would definitely buy this one again.

title: Cute and casual
text:
Love this bow assortment! It's a wonderful variety of colors in classic stripes...there is a headband to to go with every outfit! They're all well-made, with no loose threads or crooked seams. The bows are nice and straight and fluff out like they should (no drooping or having one side higher than the other). They're all made of a thick t-shirt-type material and look best with more casual outfits, which is what my nieces wear 99% of the time, so we're set! The headbands are very stretchy, and I can attest to the fact that they fit a ten-month-old pretty well, and a three-year-old perfectly.

I know (here in the South at least) some moms like BIG bows to go on their little girls' heads, but I would recommend these bows to moms who like something a little more average-sized and don't follow the huge bow trend. These are the kind I liked for my daughter, more of an accent to an outfit than a statement in and of itself. I got these for my sister's daughters, since she prefers regular-sized bows like I do.

There were six headbands in the pack, so they come in at just over $2 each, which is a good price for the quality. I would definitely get these again. I received the headbands at a discount for evaluation and review, but my opinions are 100% my own and were formed after all-day wear by my nieces and looking them over carefully.

title: Simply stunning
text: [[VIDEOID:82df42af37539876c1422290f3276bb7]] These earrings are absolutely stunning. Without a doubt they are one of the most gorgeous pieces in my growing collection. As I get older I find myself attending more events, such as weddings, fundraisers, and holiday balls, so I finally had to step up my jewelry selection and these earrings really fit the bill. They aren't so large as to be ostentatious, but thanks to the design and clarity and sparkle of the cubic zirconia they REALLY stand out when I wear them. The metal is a lovely rose gold that looks fabulous with most any color I choose to wear, and the stones shine just as much as a real diamond. They are definitely higher end and elevate whatever dress I have on. They are also very well made, with not a flaw to be found; the stones are secure and every part is precisely placed. They're also lightweight with secure clips, so I don't have to worry about them falling off or becoming uncomfortable. I received the vintage glam earrings at a discount for evaluation and review, but my opinions are 100% my own and were formed after examination and actual wear.

title: Worth The Money?
text: I have an Anuschka wallet that I bought more than five years ago and it's still one of my favorite things. I know Anuschka products are not cheap, but though I like this purse, I'm really struggling with the $238 price tag - and it's even more on other websites. I've never spent over $100 for a purse before, so perhaps that is part of the reason that I have misgivings. This purse has many pockets which is GREAT, and yes, it's very colorful and pretty. But when I see a leather purse with a high price tag that is made in a country that is also where a lot of the USA's really cheap clothing comes from, I wonder what Anuschka actually paid for materials and also to have this made. My guess is that though the purse seems high quality, I don't see how it could be. I never expected to see a "made in India" tag on the inside. The two things I really don't like about it are the plastic "feet" underneath which will scratch furniture if you set it down - I don't like feet on my handbags - and the other issue is that though there are many pockets, there is not a lot of width to fill the pockets up.  I would not buy this particular purse again.

metadata.title: Anuschka Triple Compartment Medium Satchel Purse (Lush Lilac)

title: Pretty,Stylish and Comfortable
text: I really like this shirt. It is a fashion marvel and oddity: usually the stretchy fabric is very clingy, but this shirt is not clingy at all. I don't think complete strangers would stop me to tell me how pretty it is - that would be WEIRD - but I hope one or two of my co-workers will say it's nice. My ONE issue with this shirt is that the pink floral overlay is split in the back. If you have an ample rear area, the split becomes wider, making it appear that you are stretching the shirt to capacity, when of course, you aren't because it's a stretchy shirt. I bought a 2X and it fits perfectly - a 3X would have been too big  in the arms and chest areas. I like this Allegra item and would probably buy more of their shirts, but I HOPE they consider the design flaw of this very pretty shirt.  By the way, I washed it in cold water and hung it to dry on a padded hanger (to avoid what my daughter calls "shoulder nipples" in the shirt) and it dried over night.

title: Leather Belt
text: This belt is way longer than my husband needed, but it was easy to drill extra holes to make it fit.  Since it is solid leather without any beveling, you could easily trim the pointed end shorter too, if you wanted to.  The leather seems legit rather than some bonded crud that's going to fall apart in 3 months.  I took off one star for the way the buckle is attached to the belt.  There are four stitches of red and tan thread holding it together.  They look cheesy and could be a weak point in an otherwise very sturdy belt.  I'd have rather seen some rivets there.  Other than that, its a perfectly fine belt for jeans or casual pants.

metadata.title: Men's genuine fullgrain tanned leather jeans belt with buckle

title: Beveled Edge
text: We tested 3 belts by this manufacturer and this was the only one that came with a beveled edge.  It does give a more finished, slightly dressier look to the belt but the downside is that you cannot cut the free end if you need to shorten the belt.  My husband has a 34" waist and this belt required extra holes to be drilled leaving quite a long end beyond the buckle.  As will all the belts in this line, the buckle is attached with some contrast thread stitching rather than rivets.  It looks pretty tacky and could be a point of weakness over time.  At least it appears to be made of a solid piece of leather rather than the bonded or vinyl junk so common these days.

metadata.title: Men's genuine fullgrain tanned leather jeans belt with buckle

title: Blue?
text: This belt has a distinct blue color.  I hope it will fade to more of a black with time.  The blue really makes the stitching at the buckle stand out, and not in a good way.  As others have mentioned, the leather has a toxic smell to it and needs to be aired out before it could ever be worn.  I think it might be worth trying to rub some sort of leather conditioner on this to try and darken the color and kill the smell.  On the plus side, the belt length is perfect for a 34" waist.

title: Stunning bracelet
text:
[[VIDEOID:22a1c78d8b8b3249b76c47680306a00f]] The Girl Era amethyst tennis bracelet is stunning to say the least. It comes beautifully packaged in a very nice gold box with a small gold bow. Once opening the bracelet it rests upon a black velvet piece. This is a great gift idea for Valentine's day, mothers day, your girlfriend, mom, etc..

The sparkle and shine on this bracelet is out of this world. Honestly, it's gorgeous. Although this looks sterling silver, it's not. It is a silver colored alloy. I'm not sure how it will hold up in the long term but it's working without issue for me right now. This is 7" in length so a good size to fit most wrists. The cubic zirconia diamond accents really make the amethyst pop as well. I've worn this with jeans and a nice top. It really dresses up any outfit. This bracelet will also blend well with a nice pair of earrings or would look great alone. Gorgeous bracelet. The clasp is also very well made and does not appear like one that will loosen quickly. I'm seriously in love with this and it is definitely worth the price.

Disclaimer: I received this product discounted or free in exchange for my honest and unbiased review. These thoughts are my own and are not influenced by the seller or price.

This would not be appropriate for a child. This would make a wonderful gift for valentine's day, other holidays, graduation, a "just-because" gift, birthdays (especially July!), or any other reason you can think of. It really is beautiful. title: A wonderful find!
text:
I have been collecting these abstract pattern "robes" from Novica for a couple of months now, and have amassed a nice collection of them, thanks to Amazon. In my earlier travels around the world when I was young and fleet of foot, I amassed a rather large collection of oversized, wildly patterned batik jackets and dusters...and have subsequently worn them to death over the decades.

So I have been looking for replacements that I can source from home, and was delighted to stumble upon Novica, AND to find I could order through Amazon. I shortened this wildly patterned robe (and what I received was pretty darn close to the colors shown, at least on my monitor) by about nine inches, saved the belt for something else, took off the hanging loop and the belt loops and now have a wonderfully wacky duster jacket to wear open over a black tank and black slacks. Whenever I wear ANY of the batik robes-turned jackets from my Novica selections, I always get people stopping me to ask where I got it and where they could find one like it. Fun!

Caveat: I take care with these, and spot clean only. For use as a lounging robe, it is wonderful to have a rayon garment soften with use...but for a jacket/duster to be worn as street-clothes, I don't want to have to launder this fabric, causing it to soften up.

Great fun! FANTASTIC PRINTS! Good quality fabric. Super price!

title: Beautiful Top
text:
I am normally a size 12 and really seemed to be between sizes, so I wrote to ask what size I should get. A couple of people advised getting the large, but some of the reviews suggested going up a size. In the end I just took a guess. Because it was a peplum-style top (and I once had a too-small peplum top that 'rode up' my tummy) I decided to go with the extra-large.

It's true it was a bit large - a bit. But then I washed it and put it in the dryer to try and shrink it and it shrunk just enough to where it was nearly perfect. Still a smidge loose, but honestly, I think I made the right choice, it is very flattering.

Sizing aside, I love this print. I have to be careful with prints. I don't look good in too-bright colors or high-contrast. This is small scale and elegant. The navy color goes good with everything.
