metadata.title: Happy Sailed Women Chiffon Off Shoulder Long Sleeve Halter Neck Shirt Blouse Tops, Medium Black

title: Nice make and color but not my style
text:
I've been looking for wide belts to go with Summer Maxi Skirts that I also wear as dresses - something to add the finishing touch. This looked cute and simple enough that it would match multiple items. On the plus side, this seems like a very sturdy belt. The thickness of it alone is not at all flimsy and it could definitely pass for real leather if someone wasn't inspecting it closely. The color is nice and warm, as well. However, it was a little TOO stiff and there really wasn't much give. Which may be exactly what someone else is looking for, but not so myself. Also, it was slightly wider than what I was expecting, but that is purely a matter of preference, not anything against the belt itself.

I am 5'5, 150lbs and my waist is where I carry all my weight. Usually, my pant size varies between 30/31 or size 10. I ordered the Medium and it fit right at the second notch. I could probably tighten it and fit at the third, but then it would just be cutting into my belly tub. In summary, Decent Price, Nice Color, Sturdy construction. Cons, Super stiff and wider than what I was expecting. Not a bad purchase, just not for me.

metadata.title: Womens Tan Sleek Faux Leather Belt With Oval Buckle Medium

title: Didn't fit me right, but still "okay"
text:
Okay, I REALLY love the blue and black plaid pattern. It's very stylish and I wish this dress would have worked out for me because this could be worn for so many different occasions/events/etc.I am 5'5, 154 lbs (mostly in my belly area) 36D/38C depending, I wear 30/31 pants or size 10 usually. The Pros - Great Pattern, Modest Length, Can definitely be worn with a petticoat, has a bit of stretch in the bust area. Sadly, the Cons - If you have bigger arms, the holes will fit a bit tightly, because of the extra room allowed for the bust, the upper back zipper area pops out some in an unattractive way, Fabric is a bit stiff (that might change if it's put in the wash first), no lining, no loops/string to keep belt in place, belt pops out and looks sloppy.

Personally, I still think this is an "okay" dress (still returning it, though). But I wouldn't want to wear a sweater each and every time to cover up the loose back area or to hide the fact that my arms look like stuffed sausages trying to escape their casing. Nor do I want to try and safety pin the belt every time, either. These are my own hang ups (which Is why I'm returning) but other than that, it's not a horrible garment for the price.

metadata.title: GRACE KARIN Boatneck Picnic Dress for Women 50s Sleeveless Size L BP02-16

title: Beautiful to look at, kinda rough to wear without socks.
text:
Okay. First - the good. They are absolutely adorable and fit as expected. I LOVE the embroidered design and think these are the cutest ever. The sole is soft and feels nice and you can tell it has been hand sewn into the shoe. Now, here's the bummer. The embroidered pandas are super rough feeling atop the toes. Personally, I was hoping to wear these without socks but the irritation is very noticeable and not comfortable at all. I found a "quick fix' - I have tons of fleece scraps from old projects, so I cut to shape and attached it with a thin piece of double sided tape - temporary solution for the no socks look. I didn't want to try fabric glue for something more permanent because I was afraid it would seep through the fabric of the shoe and stain/ruin the appearance. It makes walking in them more bearable but I really wish there had been a softer fabric/guard or something put in place to have prevented the irritation and the need to "fix it yourself" in the first place. Still totally love the look, just a bit frustrated about the discomfort and work on my end for a more comfortable fit.

ps - slight glue stains on the outside of shoe (in pics) but nothing that would jump out at the naked eye.

metadata.title: AvaCostume Chinese Style Panda Bamboo Embroidery Prom Dress Shoes, Blue, 38

title: Timeson Makes Great Blouses, Just not this one.
text: Oh, Timeson. *sigh*. Well, even the best have their bad days, right? I love almost all of Timeson Women's blouses. They are usually very comfortable and form flattering. I decided to give this shirt a try as I've had such wonderful luck with their other styles. For me, this was a miss. I am 5'5, 154 lbs with most of that weight in my midsection. So yes, a blouse that is looser is usually ideal, however as much as I wanted to like this item, it just did NOT lay right on me at all. Maybe on a smaller chested woman (I am 38C/36D) this would work but I just ended up looking pregnant. Which I am not. Also, there is a seam along the back of the shirt that runs across the shoulder blades. If you have gentler skin (I do) it becomes irritating real quick. It's still a well made product, covers the bum just enough, and the shipping was great, but this just didn't work for me.

title: Stylish, Warm and High-Quality Beanie That Has Plenty Of Room To Cuff Up On Even My Big Head
text:
*REVIEW OF FREE PRODUCT*

I couldn't be happier with the quality and style of this cuffed Hipster beanie. I received it in green and love the color (which looks the same as the pictured color). All the seams and stitching are perfect, and it looks well-made like it will last a long time. It's a tight smooth acrylic weave that feels soft and really comfortable. It's easy to care for as it's machine washable.

We live on the west coast and love the weight of this beanie as it's warm, but isn't bulky or too thick and heavy. With temperatures dipping into the high 30's, it's perfect for morning and evening walks. My husband who is light on hair (well, yes, bald is more accurate), loves wearing it during anytime of the day with the cooler temperatures in So Cal right now.

This beanie is unisex, and the sizing is versatile. It fits me, my husband and teen son with a snug look even though we all have different head sizes. It's perfect because there's no weird sagging, and it's long enough on each of us to wear cuffed- which reveals the stylish leather-like Hipster logo. My head is large, but this beanie could easily fit a larger head, so I think it should fit just about anyone cuffed up.

I think this Hipster acrylic beanie rivals the style and quality of big name brands I see at places like Vans (for about $22-$28) and Urban Outfitters (for about $15). The Hipster beanie comes with a $24 retail price tag attached, though the current price is so low right now (about $7 bucks depending on color) that it's a fab deal, and I can't imagine anyone regretting this purchase. I think it's a top notch 5-star beanie and a great deal at the current price. I highly recommend the Hipster beanie for yourself or as a gift.

title: Well Done For A Faux Fur Scarf & Is Soft & Warm- Short Slip Through Style & Spot Or Dry Clean Only
text: While this brown faux fur scarf isn’t exactly my style, it’s a well made piece that does look a lot like real fur. It feels really bushy and soft and adds a lot of warmth. I’m not a fashion expert, but I think it looks best under a coat that comes up over the edges as it’s thick and doesn’t hang much (it’s short) and reminds me more of a collar than scarf with how it pulls though a slit and stays close to my neck. The stitching all looks quite well done. This is a fun fashion accessory for a retro glamour look and will provide a lot of warmth in cold weather. It’s not something I’d imagine wearing often both stylistically and from a practical view as it can be spot or dry cleaned only. I’m taking a star off just because, as a matter of personal preference, I don’t love the short length and fur style on me. But it’s well done and good quality if someone is looking for a faux fur short style scarf of this type. 4 stars.

title: Fabric Is A Thicker Poly That’s Not Airy Or Breathable, Not Something I’d Wear Outside- Just OK
text:
This Orchid Row “chiffon” kimono has a nice floral print on fabric that’s 100% polyester. I don’t care for the feel of the fabric as it’s so synthetic feeling and not breathable or airy. While chiffon can be made from polyester (or silk), I think of chiffon as sheer and floaty but this polyester feels thick and heavy. It just hangs on me and lacks any movement. It doesn’t fit like in the photo or have the same sheer, flowy quality that’s pictured IMO.

This is a one size fits all garment, and I am tall at 5’11” so this kimono may fit me different than others. The sleeves barely cover my elbows, and the length just covers my knees. The top looks boxy on me and isn’t particularly flattering, though it doesn’t look bad. This has slits on the sides that go to the top of my thighs. They should give the fabric more movement but they don’t.

I’ve tried this kimono on many times over various outfits, such as a tank dress and over a tank with jeans or pants. But I’ve still never worn it. That’s a bad sign for me as I wear things right away if I like how they look and/or feel (unless I get them off season). At most, I could see wearing this at home as I think this looks like pajamas or a robe on me, yet the polyester fabric lacks the softness or comfort I want for hanging out at home. This is just okay. 3 stars.

metadata.title: Orchid Row Women's Printed Maxi Chiffon Kimono Ruana Wraps

title: Cute Lightweight Summer Top-I Like It But Sized Small For XL Especially In Armholes & Shoulders
text:
Sonja B. is a brand I like as the few tops I have are better quality and more stylish than expected for such an affordable clothing line. This babydoll top looks 70’s retro cute to me and is nice and lightweight for summer. It’s made of 100% polyester, but mimics the look of cotton well without dealing with the wrinkles. I like the red color and pattern, the elastic bib design, ruffle trim at the armholes and lace trim around the bottom. This is machine washable, but needs to be line dried.

I’m 5’11” so this may fit others differently, but this shirt is nowhere near as long on me as on the model, and I’d like the shirt to be a longer. It covers my mid section, but doesn’t come down to the the top of my thighs and doesn’t hang down in back enough to cover my butt or come close to tunic length (which would be really cute). The neckline comes up high on me and isn’t flattering. And this top runs really small in certain places for an XL. The arm holes are much too tight on me (odd as that’s not where I carry my extra weight) and the shoulders are too narrow. I can cram into it, but the small arm holes would dig in and be uncomfortable to wear.

When comparing it to conventional women’s sizing, this top fits more like a size M (about a size 8/10) in the armholes and shoulders and more like a size L (about a size 12) in the body. The sizing seems disproportionate even to itself, and the overall size just doesn’t fit like an XL (about a size 14/16). In conventional sizing, I bounce between size L and XL, and XL is usually roomy on me. I’d rate this top 4 stars as I think it’s cute and reasonably well made so I like it. But I’m taking off a star because the sizing is too far off, especially in the armholes. 3 stars.

title: Too Delicate & Short For Me-But Darling Budget Necklace For Someone Young Or Petite (4.5 Stars)
text: This costume jewelry gold color necklace is really cute with a faux pearl (bead) in a heart-shaped cage and a small faux pearl (bead) hanging from a 2” chain that drops from the cage. This necklace is delicate and made of lightweight materials. This chain is only 15-1/2” long, though it can lengthen to 17-1/2” with the attached 2” extender. This necklace has nice details for a budget piece, such as a little heart at the end of the extender and a lobster claw clasp instead of a little “O” ring closure.  I’m 5’11” and in my 50’s and would wear this even though the style is young, but it looks too petite and short on me. But I do think it’s a darling budget necklace (currently $16.99) for a preteen, teen or someone petite. On that basis, I’m rating it 4.5 stars.

title: Thick & Comfortable Well Made Leggings, Cute Mesh & Printed Details-XL Fits True To Size
text:
These Due East work out pants or leggings looked small at first glance, but when I tried them on I was pleasantly surprised that the XL is a good fit and runs true to size. These are thick and provide full coverage (other than the mesh). They have a lot of stretch, but the material fits close to my body and holds me in without feeling binding. These allow for good movement and feel comfortable. I’m 5’11” and these leggings are high waisted on me, and hit me about an inch above my ankles. The waist could be turned down if too high. These leggings don’t have a waist pocket.

I like the see through mesh detail and bright pattern that I think looks more tropical than like a “maple leaf” pattern. Either way, it’s cute and perfect for a walk or jog on the beach or other activities. I do feel the colored pattern make my legs looks shorter and heavier even though I’m tall and wear a 35” inseam in regular pants. The pattern will be more flattering when I lose about 20 pounds, but that’s my own issue of needing to lose weight and not a dislike of the pattern. These leggings look well made and should hold up so long as washed on a cold, delicate cycle and I’m drying mine flat (though the tag says tumble dry on low). I like them. 4.5 stars.

metadata.title: Due East Apparel Women’s High Waist Printed Yoga Pants with Mesh Panel Tummy Control Full-Length Workout Leggings

title: Opaque So Add Some Warmth & Cover Flaws, Cute w/ Dresses & Can Wear Sandals & Open Toe Shoes
text:
These Wili W footless 70 denier nylon/spandex tights (2 pairs) are opaque enough to cover my pasty white legs and flaws like broken veins. But these aren’t total blackout tights like the 100 denier tights I buy from Nordstrom, so some skin color does show through. I wear open toe shows and sandals most of the year, which I can’t wear with regular tights. So I really that I can wear these footless tights with dresses and still wear the shoes I like to wear most. These give me good coverage and some warmth, and these are fashionable while being much more comfortable and less formal than pantyhose.

These tights are good quality. They feel smooth and the seams look and feel strong. I wore a pair one day and didn’t get any snags, so these should last for multiple uses (though I’m not sure how many yet). These tights seem true to size. I’m 5’11” and these hit me just a little above the ankles and the top goes all the way up to my natural waist. I’d expect to wear a size XL, and the size XL is indeed a good fit. The waist felt a little tight as I was pulling these up over my currently chunky thighs, but once on these aren’t binding or uncomfortable and offer good control so they’re smooth and slimming under a dress. I really like these footless tights a lot. 5 stars.

metadata.title: WiliW Women's Footless Tights Black Control Top Opaque Pantyhose 2 Pairs Hold & Stretch XL

title: Faux Cashmere Pashmina Good For Layering When Chilly & Easy To Stow In My Bag
text: This faux cashmere pashmina is made of a soft and smooth fabric. It feels like a synthetic blend, but there no tag or indication of what it’s made of and also no care instructions. I received one that’s solid grey on one side and solid black on the other. It has short fringe at the edge. The weather where I live only gets cold enough for a coat for 5 minutes and the  I’m stuck lugging it around. I prefer just wearing a scarf or wrap and gloves that I can just stow in my backpack when that chill is gone. This pashmina works well as I can wear it hanging like a scarf or wrapped around my shoulders so it hangs long in the front but short in the back. This pashmina is flat and isn’t bulky or heavy, but still adds a nice extra layer of warmth. I love black and gray accessories, and the grey/black color combo is practical and compliments a lot of my wardrobe. I like it. 4 stars.

title: Cozy But Not Too Bulky Or Heavy & Reasonably Well Made-Run Big, Stretch Out & Need To Hand Wash
text:
I received 5 pairs of the style A9 socks. These are cozy socks without being too heavy and bulky, and I like wearing them for the cool mornings and evenings we’ve been having in So Cal. They feel soft enough (though I have softer socks), the color assortment is good and the socks look reasonably well made with few stray threads. The patterns are basic and kind of masculine and could easily be worn by men. These are a crew sock height on me.

The A9 socks run really big. The stated range is a women’s shoe size 5-9. I wear a women’s 10 in open toe shoes and 10.5 or 42 Euro in closed toe shoes, yet these border on being too roomy for me. And while they fit okay at first, these stretch out a lot and also slide down. These seem better sized for women in the 9-12 shoe size range (or for men). These are fairly good socks, but they run big and stretch out bigger. And the directions say to hand wash when these are just basic socks. All things considered, these are just okay. 3 stars.

metadata.title: 5 Pairs Winter Merino Wool Socks for Women Thick Cozy Socks Knit Warm Socks for Women Christmas Gifts

title: Nice Design w/ Ample NonSlip Silicone, Breathable Cotton Blend, Fit My Size 10 Feet Below Ankle
text:
These are good nonslip socks for exercise and/or safety when walking on slippery hard flooring. I received a 3-pack in a nice color assortment of pink, purple and khaki. These look good on with a decorative stripe that crosses the top and surrounds the heel, and the nonslip bottoms are particularly grippy with better than usual coverage with silicone features. These have diamonds and the Giotto name underfoot and an attractive tulip in nonslip silicone under on each heel. The breathable stretch cotton blend is absorbent and comfortable.

The stated size range is a woman’s shoe size 5.5-9. I wear a shoe size 10 to 10.5, so I fall outside the range. Still, the foot gives me enough room and these are a comfortable fit. These appear to be more low cut on me and come up just under the ankle, likely because my feet are bigger than the stated range. But the fit is secure and the back at the heel doesn’t slip down. The quality is good with minimal stray threads and nicely finished edges and seams. I’ve machine washed and dried my socks a few times so far, and they still look like new. These are good nonslip socks. Recommended. 4.5 stars.

title: Not Relaxed Like Photo & Run Way Too Small, Cheap Fabric Lacks Any Give Or Softness, Dated Design
text:
These pants leave me almost speechless. I really dislike the fabric, fit and design. The fabric feels and looks cheap, and these are crinkly and rough with no softness at all. The fabric has no give or stretch to it. There are some lovely polyester blends, but this isn’t one of them and it’s hard to believe this has any cotton in the blend. The fabric doesn’t look or feel pleasing.

Also, the fit is terribly small. These are described as “loose” and look relaxed and baggy in the stock photo. I can barely pull the XL on and they’re so skin tight and short I could never wear these, even though I normally wear size L or XL. Finally, given the tight fit and low quality fabric, the design looks dated and unattractive. I dislike these pants a lot. 1.5 stars.

title: Absolutely Worth It!!❤️
text: I ordered this in the rose gold “I love you to the moon and back” with the personalized engraving. I ordered this for a week old kitten I rescued and bottle fed during a very difficult time in my life. Her name was Bonita, a very beautiful calico. I am disabled and she was my constant companion for 15.5 years. We were so bonded, both our days were never complete unless she stretched out on me, putting her little heart on mine so they could beat together. She died November 4, 2018 one year ago tomorrow.💔 I originally ordered this necklace hoping it would arrive before the first anniversary of her death, as it feels I’ve been holding my breath this entire year, waiting for that date to come. To my surprise, when I ordered it, it was set to arrive between my birthday in October and November 4th. It arrived on my birthday, I was feeling particularly blue, 44 was hard for me. Unfortunately, when I opened it, it was in yellow gold and had the name “Jamar” on the back. My heart sank. Not just for Bonita but mostly because I thought Jamar was more than likely a persons name and someone out there had received my necklace instead, I felt very sad for them!😔 I immediately contacted the seller and they apologized profusely!! The only thing they asked of me was to send them a picture of the necklace. I did just that and they sent out my original order immediately with a ship to date of, you guessed it, November 4th, the one year anniversary of my beloved Baby Bonita’s death. The necklace arrived early, again and it’s beautiful!! I don’t really like the chain, I make jewelry so I know that you can just twist the jump ring and take the pendants off to switch the chain out if you’d like to switch the chain out to a higher quality chain. As for the pendants, they are made of very good quality and the engraving is also done very well. I would highly recommend this product for cremains of a beloved fur-baby or a loved one. It’s discreet enough that you’ll know what it is but others won’t and it’s also stylish. I hope you’ll cherish yours as much as I cherish mine, I now have my baby next to my heart forever, right where she always wanted to be. Thank you.❤️

title: Great Purchase! Size down for yoga
text: First of all, I love this shirt! It's super comfy and cute. I can't believe how cheap it was! At that price, I expected it to fall apart in the washer, but I've washed it multiple times now, and it's holding up perfectly (I don't dry it). The neckline is a little higher than expected, but it still looks really nice. I have worn it out for drinks a couple times, either with no bra or a bralette (pictured here braless), and I have gotten tons of compliments each time. I originally bought this to wear to yoga, but the medium was a little loose and would slide up during inversions. I will probably keep the medium to wear casually and purchase another one in a size small for yoga. As a reference, I'm 5'4", 150 lbs, 34/36B bust size. If you're getting this for everyday wear, or any work-out that doesn't involve you being upside down, it is very true to size, but if you specifically want it for yoga, I would recommend sizing down.

title: Great yoga socks!
text:
These are absolutely wonderful socks for yoga! I also recommend them for weight lifting for those who prefer to take their shoes off for a flatter foot. I love them! There is absolutely no skidding or sliding whatsoever and the sock hugs the middle area of your foot which I love because it keeps my feet from cramping during certain stances. I use sliding disks when working out, I put my feet on them and slide them back and forth for a great core workout and these keep them from sliding out from under my feet which is amazing. I have a hard time doing this with tennis shoes so I decided to give it a try with just socks on and any other sock causes them to slide out from under me and I almost always get hurt. So these are just great socks! Oh and the tongue on the back helps to prevent blisters from your tennis shoes as well.

Pros: great grip, socks hug tightly to your foot, great for yoga or weightlifting without shoes.

Cons: none

title: Too thin, comfortable though
text: Firstly let me say these are one of the softest pair of leggings I’ve ever tried on. They are definitely buttery soft. They slid right on with ease and were a pleasure to have against my skin! So comfortable! Second, these are not made for runners. I have learned a thing or two over the years and that is that you need a super tight wide band around your waist when it comes to leggings you wear to the gym IF you plan to run. I’m a runner. These just weren’t it for me. I could wear them all day as casual leggings and maybe even on a bike. But they are not made for running or using the elliptical. They are super thin, compressive but thin. For example: the squat test failed as you can see in the picture. The white card paper is showing right through without a flash on. Also, I wore them to the gym and first attempted to run and unfortunately I kept stopping to pull them up because they were sliding down off of my belly and my shirt was exposing my stomach. So after about the 10th time I decided to stop all together and try the elliptical instead. Again, the same thing happened. Not as often but it still happened and I got so annoyed that I changed out of them. I am going to use these as fall leggings or comfort leggings instead.

title: Fun and easy to use!
text:
These were great fun for my daughter's birthday party at the rollerskating rink! They came with a safety strip that prevented them from turning on during transit and they were super easy for the kids to figure out once they were ready to use them. The on/off switch was fairly easy to use and the rubbery band made it easy to put on and take them off. The variety of colors are great and the lights shine bright like a diamond but the battery life averaged at around 3 hours.

Pros: So much fun, colorful lights, easy to use, affordable
Cons: Low battery life (~3 hour average)

title: Runs large, cute budget friendly summer cover up
text:
This dress is a really simple but cute summer cover up.
Runs large so order a size or two down.
I'm 5'8" and it stops a little above my knees. It's longer than I thought it would be but not too long by any means.
The material is that lightweight, springy, soft material. It shows a lot of creases (was very wrinkled right out of the bag) but in black the creases arent super obvious. The tassels are all bunched up (see pic - don't mind PJ pants underneath 😉), thought they would be that shiny thin material but they look like regular cotton so they bunch up on the packaging ... Again, not a deal breaker bc I'm using it as a cover up.
Could be paired with a cute hat for a fun summer look! Overall, for under $20 I'm pleased and look forward to using it this summer!

metadata.title: Romwe Women's v-Neck Solid Sleeveless Short Straight Dress, Black, Small

title: Fits cute, material is questionable
text:
Hmmm ... what to do about this dress ...
Fit is definitely cute! Its a little big under the arms but purchasing a smaller size would mean tight in the chest and the rest of the dress. It's under the arms anyway so no one can see it. Pockets are cute and overall fit is good. I'm 5'9 and length was just right.
I'm not sure if I'll be keeping this dress though only because of the material. Its that material that shows creases and folds. Out of the bag you can see where it was folded, and I don't mean nice crisp fold lines, I mean when the material gets a little "dark" on the fold line - and the lines are all over - borderline would only use it around the house kind of lines. Pretty sure its going to be difficult to never have those lines especially after washing it. I don't want to try to iron it out bc I'm afraid of what that might do to the material and then I might not be able to return. So I'm not sure ... not super expensive but for just over $21 and not sure how the material will hold up, it might wind up as a return.

title: Good combo of sexy and modest!
text:
I really like this swimsuit, it's so adorable! I purchased this so I'd have something a little more modest than my teeny bikini's to wear to the preschooler birthday parties this summer without scaring the other parents ;). It's cute but a little sexy so I don't feel overly "mom-ish!" the fabric is a decent thickness and the liner is good quality. I also enjoy that the skirt isn't too long, again, I can be more modest without totally looking like a grandma out there with the kids. The neckline might be a little low, and offer minimal support for someone with larger breasts, but I'm only a b-cup so have no issues with it, personally. A small opening at the top of the breast cups allow for pad removal or adjustment. There are two sets of ties, one around the neck which is typical, but a second set around the waste is very appreciated, helps with the overall fit of the swimsuit since it's hard to make a one size fits most for women (especially after child bearing years). This fits as expected in all areas. My only complain is that the cut on the skirt portion looks a little unfinished, no stitch/sewn close which makes a little nervous after a bunch of wear/washes. Overall, a great find or such a great price!

*I purchased this product at a discounted rate in exchange for an honest review after use*

title: Nice Mat...
text:
I was looking for a mat this size for a decent price and was happy when I saw this on Amazon for $10 after searching the site for a couple of hours. Once I got the mat, I was excited to use it in my bathroom. However, I was quite disappointed to see the permanent indentation down the middle because of how it was packaged. It was delivered in a slim box, folded in half causing unappealing fold lines down the middle (reason for 4 stars instead of 5). I tried pressing around the line with my fingers to see if I can get it to fill in a bit but, it didn't work.

I really like the mat but, I don't like how the fold lines make it look (see photo). I am thinking about returning it but, not sure yet. This should be delivered in a box slightly bigger than the mat so that it doesn't need to be folded for shipping. Or, possibly rolled up in a tube to prevent the fold lines. At least if it came rolled, it can always be rolled the opposite way to straighten it out or let it happen in time after use (stepping on it).

Update 12/5/2016: Changed rating from 4 to 5 stars. I contacted the seller about the fold lines in the mat I received. Seller responded promptly and immediately sent a replacement mat in a bigger box that was not folded (See second photo). Would definitely recommend!

title: Cleverly designed, quality leather belt for a surprisingly low price.
text:
This is a very nice genuine leather belt at a bargain price. The belt is much more adjustable than a traditional belt with holes and a prong. It also looks classy and has many buckle designs to choose from. I wasn't sure what kind of quality I could get for $9.99 including shipping and a nice box, but I was very pleasantly surprised.

The belt uses a ratchet system to tighten. On the back of the belt, from about 4 to 13 inches from the tip there is a strip of plastic sewn into the leather that has a sawtooth pattern. That catches a spring tensed metal latch on the buckle when tightening the belt. There is a small lever on the bottom of the buckle that releases the latch from the sawteeth when you want to loosen the belt. The sawteeth are about a quarter inch apart so the belt is much more adjustable than a standard belt. You also won't have the problem of wearing the leather out by pulling the end back to fit the prong into a belt hole. The belt is 53 inches long and will need to be cut to fit your size.

I just got the belt so I'm not sure about its durability. I suppose it is possible that the plastic sawteeth could wear out or chip off. However, I really like what I have so far and would highly recommend this belt.

title: Lovely, fresh and light!
text:
I'm very, very happy I bought this maxi dress!

So, yes, technically it's not perfect - it lacks darts and the slides&rings on the straps are made of plastic and sooner than later they may brake - BUT nonetheless the dress is very nice and I like it a lot. A lot A LOT.

I bought an XL because I wanted to be sure (as sure you can be when you buy online) to have the flow and airiness that I wanted - and I got it.
The fabric is light and fresh, and a lovely shade of dusty light blue. The straps are adjustable and it has pockets!

It's a super simple dress, but the loose fit and baggy shape gives it a little something extra that - in my opinion - makes it stand out against the straight maxi dresses.
By the way, I feel the simplicity of it makes it quite easy to adapt it from an everyday-around-the-house dress to something a little more elegant for a summer evening with just the help of some accessories.

As a note, in the photos I'm wearing it with slippers and no bra, and the strap are adjusted as long as possible. For reference, I'm 5'4", 125 pounds and 36B.

title: Cute!!
text:
Few months ago I bought from Hiking World a black&white striped skirt and a couple of days ago they kindly sent me for free the top that matches the skirt to review it, even if a) I've never done it before and b) I don't know if I have a sense of fashion. So, bear with me and here I go.

Being quite insecure with my body and based on the photos of the top alone (modeled by a girl that probably is half my age and a third of my size), I wasn't sure what to expect - but I was pretty surprised when I received it and tried it on.

I asked for a large, because I'm not fond of clothes that stick too much to my body and judging by how the top fits me, I would say it's true to size. It's loose enough, comfy, soft, feels good and - when paired with certain clothes - doesn't makes me feel uneasy.
Don't get me wrong, it is short - laid flat, the large is 16" long by 15.5" wide - but I gave it a go with different possible pairings to see how versatile it could be and I found out that it seems to work well with different styles.
Also, the fabric is 100% modal, not see through and stretchy.

For reference, I'm 5'4", 125 pounds, 36B. I'm attaching few photos to give an idea of what I'm talking about - hope they help to decide if the top may work for you or not. I tried it with the striped skirt, shorts, high waist pants, a maxi skirt and - bonus! - being loose enough, the size large allowed me to layer the top on a tank top and I used it to do yoga!

If you have questions, I'll be happy to answer :) !

title: NOT 20-30 mmHg! More like 8-15 mmHg, or a good pair of workout tights.
text:
These are fine compression leggings if you only need mild compression, like you'd get from a good pair of workout tights. They are not fit for medical use.

I have POTS and have been buying the 20-30 mmHg stockings sold on Amazon by Briteleaf, which work quite well for me, but I thought it would be nice to try a pair of footless ones instead of just open toe, as I have problems with the foot part bunching in my boots sometimes.

These were a complete waste of money for me. They're not even skin-tight all the way up--I have regular leggings that are tighter--much less providing adequate compression. They're fine leggings, but I have plenty of leggings--I need graduated 20-30 mmHg compression, like the title said these were.

It may be possible to size down and get good compression in these, but I'm already wearing the smallest size.

Now I have to pay for 1-day shipping for another pair from Briteleaf so I can stop feeling awful, and I'm out the money for these, which were more expensive!

Please, be responsible and change the title to reflect your product accurately!

title: NOT UPF 50. PROVIDES LITTLE TO NO PROTECTION AGAINST UVA.
text:
Everything but the visor part itself is made of a gauzy mesh that provides exactly as much UV protection as it looks like it would.

How do I know? I have lupus, and after wearing it outside for 20 minutes I was horribly sick--about the same as if I didn't wear any cover-up, whereas a regular hoodie lessens it and real UPF 50+ fabric basically prevents it.

I have no idea whether this will help prevent sunburn, but I can tell you that sunburn is caused by UVB rays and my immune response is caused by UVA rays, which are also the ones that cause premature aging.

So if other people are saying that this works because they haven't gotten sunburnt, their skin could be getting aged while they wear this thing and they wouldn't even know it.

There are many true UPF 50+ products on the market. Buy one of them.

title: Cute dress
text:
Length
This is a nice, simple dress. I am 5’2” and hoped that based on the other reviews that it shrinks in the wash that it would fit perfectly. It is close, but still a little long. I’m guessing it would be a perfect length (for me that is almost to the floor) for someone who is about 5’5”.
Quality
I washed before wearing and when it came from the wash, it had some “pilling”, those little fabric balls on the bottom third of the skirt. The fabric is not a great quality. I don’t know how long this dress will last because of the fabric quality.
Pockets
I was thrilled that it had pockets, but they are not very deep. I have another dress with pockets that are a bit deeper and I love it. My iPhone 8+ (granted it is a HUGE phone) was protruding from the pocket.
Final thoughts
This is a cute dress. I love the empire waist. I received a number of compliments when I wore it. I hope the fabric holds up. Based on everything, I would probably buy again. If the fabric was a little better, it would be a no brainer.

title: Size chart found with item photos is misleading
text:
The pants look as described and appear well made. I followed their size chart found with the photos, but they ended up being way too big. I ordered the XXL, because their size chart indicated this as a match for my size. They are long; I'm 5'7" tall -inseam 31"- and the XXL definitely covered my feet and then some. The weight of the lace bell-bottoms tend to pull the pants downward -they need to fit snug but not tight to stay up properly. Other reviewers stated these pants have a 'lot of stretch' to them. Believe the reviews!
My advice is to order at least one size down from their measurements' recommendations. I am reordering these in a size large. Would have been 5+ stars if the sizing wasn't so off.

Update 2 weeks later:
Received the exchange; they fit so much better! From XXL down to size L.

title: Fit and feel like cotton athletic socks
text:
I have a few clothing items made from merino wool that I use for camping/backpacking. It's not as scratchy as other wools - soft like cotton, but still with the warmth and water-resistance one expects from wool. I prefer 100% merino wool stuff - socks + base layer - for cold weather camping.

These socks are a merino wool-synthetic blend. They are still soft and weather-resistant but not especially warm. It's honestly hard to distinguish them from the cotton-poly moisture-wicking Hanes socks I've got in my drawer, at least in terms of fit and feel.

Short story: I can't say anything bad about these socks, but these aren't for cold weather.

title: Comfortable and Flattering
text: Since gaining a few pounds,  I've had an incredibly hard time finding comfortable and flattering jeans. These pajama jeans don't pinch or pull and have a rise that's high enough to conceal any roundness you might be self conscious about... Without that "mom jean" look or feel.  I've bought just about every style available from Pajama Jean and plan on donating all my traditional jeans. But like other reviewers,  the waist is a bit of a struggle to get over the hips the first time. I can't see a way around this for the manufacturer without compromising how comfortable they are. But like all jeans,  with a little wear,  loosen up a bit and become easier to pull up throughout the day. I wear a size 8 and ordered medium.  They fit perfectly.

title: This necklace looks classy and timeless
text:
This heart necklace is a nice, classy looking piece of jewelry. It comes packed in a white gift box. The smaller silver heart is engraved with the words "Love you forever" on the outside, so it is hidden until you pull it out from the bigger heart. The bigger heart has two rows of the Swarovski crystals all the way around it. The chain is a lighter weight chain, but with the weight of the pendant it lays nicely. The chain is about 17-1/2". There is a drop chain where the necklace ends meet, with a tiny heart shaped pendant on it. You could also use this drop chain to make the necklace longer. The crystals are clear and pick up the reflection of lights well. This necklace looks similar to more expensive necklaces I have seen advertised by jewelers.

title: Beautiful Swarovski necklace
text:
I have several pieces of Swarovski jewelry, but this one is my favorite. The necklace arrived wrapped in plastic, inside a nice white git box. The plastic around the necklace gives an initial reaction of a cheaper quality item. However, once I took the necklace from the plastic wrapper, I was very pleased with it. The center of the pendant is a brilliant light blue color. This blue crystal is surrounded by 4 clear crystal covered "swirl"s- it definitely has some bling. The crystals are secured in a quality way, as there is no noticeable glue anywhere. This pendant is large enough to be an eye catcher, but still small enough to be tasteful. It has some weight to it to it so it stays in place. The chain is about 17" long (or it can be made longer with the extra chain), so it hangs to a good length on the neck - not too long or short. The chain will stay secured with the lobster claw clasp on it. I have only had this necklace a short time, but have already received a number of compliments on it.

title: Light and sturdy
text:
These are my first folding trekking poles, and I like these so much better than my old aluminum telescoping poles. The shafts fold much shorter (15") than my old poles (over 25") which means I'm so much more likely to bring these poles along on casual hikes since they fit completely inside my day pack. Also, a huge plus is that they'll easily fit inside my carry on bag when I'm traveling. These poles are also easy to hight-adjust since once you assemble the three parts; there is only one hight adjustment to make instead of two on a telescoping pole.

The composite shaft helps to make these very light. Each pole is 211g/7.44oz without tips or baskets. I like that they seem very sound -- they don't rattle or buzz when you plant. I'm 6'0" and these are the perfect size for me: I set the length at 120-123 CM and still can shorten 5 CM when going uphill. My wife is 5'6" and 115 CM is good for normal walking but there's no room to go shorter than 115CM for uphill. I wouldn't recommend these poles for anyone shorter than 5'6".

The wrist straps are not padded like the ones on my old poles, but these straps are very smooth and soft which seems okay. I have walked about 6 miles with these and they haven't given me any problems. The straps are easy to adjust -- just pull on the loose end to tighten. The foam hand grips seem very comfortable. These poles came complete with rubber tips, three basket sizes: 2", 3.5" and 4" diameter, a handy storage bag, and two elastic bands, which are handy keeping the poles together when not using the storage bag.

Keep on trekkin'!

** Note: Yes, Amazon sent me this item for review, but the review is completely based on my own experience. Thanks for reading my review **

title: Absolutely beautiful, just somewhat lacking....
text: This watch is absolutely gorgeous - the style is can be casual or dressy, the watch faces can be changed, the band is comfortable and sleek. That being said - this is a very expensive watch.....and while the price tag definitely is associated with the Marc Jacobs brand there are some features that one would expect would be more streamlined given the price. I recieved this product in return for my honest review, but had i paid full price I would probably be a bit annoyed. As someone who has been a long time Fitbit user, I was hoping that this would be a more stylish version of what I have become accoustomed to with my other trackers. Unfortunately, there is a lot the needs to be “cleaned up” with the GoogleWear app (this is the associated tracking app) which really makes me uneasy about the validity and consistency of the tracking results. The watch is beautiful and the touch screen is very responsive, yet it is also very large. Coming from the Fitbit Alta, I had a hard time getting used to this watch. I do have naturally small wrists and the watch face just completely covered my whole wrist. Additionally, the band came undone several times (negative) but the watch wasn’t even the slightest bit damaged or scratched after falling both on a concrete basement floor and in a parking lot (positive)! However, the unsteadiness of the band made me really uneasy about wearing it (given the price) which pretty much takes away from the intended functionality.  All in all - absolutely beautiful - and such an attractive concept - just needs some work on the band design and adjustment and wish the associated app was stronger.

title: Very nice quality.
text:
Product: Men’s Fashion Braided Leather Wrap Wrist Bracelet
By: Zhenhui
Pros: Two colors (black & brown), genuine leather, metal clasps, unique design
Cons: -

My Experience:
I like the look of nice leather bracelets; it is the casual, rugged impression that lends a nice touch to a casual outfit. And, it is kind of sexy. :) The only thing that really messes up the vibe is a badly made bracelet or one made of plastic trying to be leather. Right out of the pouch, Zhenhui’s leather bracelets are attractive and the quality is clear. Plus, they have that amazing leather scent…

They come in two sizes (8” and 8.2”), so it’s possible to share with someone else whose wrist may be a bit larger/smaller. I adjusted mine to fit my wrist a little better. I am not sure that it is something that is meant to be done or simply possible because of the stainless steel clasp’s design. It was easy to do and did not damage either of the bracelets.

The embellishments are unique and encourage others to look at them and I’ve received so many complements on them! I especially like that they look great on any gender.

Zhenhui makes the following claims about their Men’s Fashion Braided Leather Wrap Wrist Bracelet:
Material: brown leather, black leather, raw leather, stainless steel clasp. (True)
Size: one length is 8 inch, one length is 8.2 inch. (True)
Perfect Match: Pack of 2 pcs. (True)

Conclusion:
Zhenhui’s braided leather bracelets are attractive, made to last, are unique, and add an additional “pop” to a casual look. I believe they would make an excellent gift for anyone who likes unique jewelry and cool, understated fashions. The leather is soft enough not to irritate or appear to be stiff, but sturdy enough that you do not have to watch your every move while wearing them. Overall, I am very pleased with this purchase, and would recommend to anyone who is searching for a thoughtful gift or distinctive bracelet.

title: A New Twist
text: I love little things out of the ordinary like these glasses.  Something different from everyone else, I don't follow trends well. Lol. They are sturdy and has a close fit. Or my head is just big. :). They are great in the sun, not overly blue and just brightens everything. I have extremely sensitive eyes so if these didn't reflect the harmful rays, I would know!  I normally wear Oakley and the comparison is close. Very close. My eyes feel relaxed and comfortable. I'm not having to squint and they do not distort color, which I love about them. The frames are sleek and strong and will absolutely hold up to me, and that's saying a lot, I'm clumsy and hard on things. I am always dropping my glasses, I put them on my head and forget them. The next thing I know I'm bumping them on something. The case is well built as well. Lined with a velvet cover to protect the lenses and a magnetic closure that works oh so well. I couldn't even get it to stay open long enough to snap a picture of the inside before they snapped shut. I would recommend these sunglasses to anyone in my family or abroad. I did receive a bit of a discount, not too much for my honest and unbiased opinion of the glasses and that is absolutely what you got. I would buy again at full price. I found a pair of Costo glasses similar to these several months back and fell in love with them but the price......whew, I just could NOT see paying over $200 for a pair of sunglasses that were subjected to my abuse.

title: Great slide on men's sneakers/slippers!
text:
These sneakers are great. I got them for my dad who is retired and fishes everyday and lives in crocs. He even considers his crocs dress shoes so I was a bit worried he wouldn't expand his shoe collection. I saw these and thought they were at least a bit nicer looking than crocs and I'd give it a try. To my surprise when I handed them to him he really liked them. I tried explaining they were sneaker slippers which means he could wear them as sneakers or slippers. He tried them on and they are true to size, they fit him great. After he wore them all night he said they were comfortable but they were hot. I was surprised he said they were hot because they are supposed to be breathable. However, today was a very humid day in Va, and he usually lives in crocs so I think anythin received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest review.g would have felt hot to him which is why I am still giving these 5 stars. They are very plain and nice looking men's shoes and he is a bit overweight with a back problem so they are great since they are slide on. I would def recommend these based on his view of them. Just note they may be a little hot.

title: A purse for chicken lovers!
text:
[[VIDEOID:beb97641d1687557bc910d89f1c908c]] It’s pretty tough not to smile when looking at this purse! This purse looks just like the advertised photo and is chicken lovers friendly.

It’s not an especially large purse, but it could hold keys, a wallet, and a phone fine. It’s very lightweight and the strap adjusts to size. There’s also a little open side pocket that could fit something small too.

It’s not the highest quality, but it’s an affordable price, so I think you’re getting what you pay for here. The zipper feels a little like it could break easily, so I’d try to be careful when opening and closing it.

Otherwise, it’s a perfect purse for chicken fans!

title: As much as I absolutely love this....
text: This by far is my favorite kigurumi to wear.. I wear it often as pajamas. Now there are many reasons for the low score, I'll explain. Reason 1)Upon arrival the costume was basically just shoved into the authentic typical "kigurumi bag" as if it either had been returned or just mistreated or something. Even the label that goes around the costume was all torn and what not. 2)Mistakenly I disregarded this (I wish I had taken pictures hindsight is 20/20) excites to try it on, and after getting it on I noticed the stitching was completely off in the crotch area and there was a huge hole. I then went online to Amazon to see if I could set up an even exchange. 3)Seeing as that wasnt an option and seeing as the seller had raised the price from only 49.99 to 79.99, I reluctantly fixed the stitching in the crotch myself. 4) after fixin and washing the costume only 1 time, the stuffing in the tail got all screwed up and got all stuffed into a tiny ball into the end of the tail. 5) at this point this was the straw that broke the camel's back, I contacted the seller in Hope's that they would do something.. anything to work with me.. and at the time I had several pictures of almost everything that had gone on minus the initial opening of the package, I'm sad to say I have since lost those pictures because I got a new phone and my old one was destroyed.  But I sent many pictures to the seller which really just turned out to be a waste of my time and data. The seller was completely unhelpful, refused to do an even exchange for me even though he had just change the price then day after I purchased mine, and refused to make it right and send me a new one.  As cute as this costume is.. I sincerely dont reccomend and would definitely not purchase this costume or from this seller ever again.

title: Good mittens, misleading listing
text:
Good mittens, but the listing is misleading. The title says "2-pair," and the photo shows two pairs. I received one pair. Which is reasonable considering the price.

The mittens are 100% cotton. They have a quilted cotton fleece lining. The exterior is thick and feels almost as durable as canvas, but is still flexible. After washing and drying they measure about 8 inches from the top of the cuff to the top of the middle finger area. The elastic cuff is about 2 inches wide.

Since they are 100% cotton I'm not sure they'd be suitable for extreme cold. And they certainly won't repel water. But they are warm in cool temperatures. And possibly usable in warmer weather too.

title: Too See-Through
text: This blouse is light, pretty, and feminine. I'm 5"2, petite, and in between a small and a medium; the medium size fits me perfectly, just like the model pictured. I like that it offers a casual, bohemian look that pairs very well with jeans, but it's nice enough to also be worn in more formal settings; I think it would go well with some skirts. [Although my fiance did say it looked "like a weird medieval peasant wedding gown" when he first saw me in it.] Its light layers are breezy and cool. The problem is that, even though there is another layer sewn beneath the very sheer outer layer, it's still pretty see-through. If you wear a darker bra under it, the bra will be very visible even from some distance, and even a white bra can be seen through it. So unless you want to be REALLY bohemian, you'll have to wear a tank top underneath. Also, I find the sleeves a bit weird. They're quite tight around the wrists, and the sleeve material is almost transparent, so your arms show through in a way that just looks sort of strange. Even though I almost like it a lot, because of its design, I'm probably not going to end up wearing this blouse all that much.

I can see what he means, because the dimensions do make them look a little weird. The material is comfortable, and these would be a breathy pair of shorts to exercise in if not for the uncomfortable tightness. Made of 93% polyester and 7% spandex, they feel almost like a pair of swim trunks. They do seem like they would keep you dry while working out. title: Cute costume, but waist band size is off
text: Since I'm a boring working mom who doesn't sew and doesn't have a crafty bone in her body, I bought this scrub/coat set for my 6 year old for Halloween this year so he could be a doctor (I bought a stethoscope separately).  He's autistic and Halloween can be very tricky because he is very sensitive about things he wears (masks are completely out of the question).  He's very average in terms of height, weighs 50 lbs and has a lean, muscular build.  I ordered the M 6x-8 size.  In terms of length, I'd say everything is about right for that size.  I expected that I would have to roll up the pant legs and possibly the coat arms, but the waist band size is almost too small for a 6 y/o and would be crazy tight on an 8 year old.  They really missed the mark on the elastic waist which is why I docked a couple stars.  I don't think it will be too uncomfortable on my son to wear for parties and trick or treating, but it's definitely snug.  For sure size up if you're in doubt, even if you have to hem or roll up arms and legs!  Also, I was a little disappointed that the coat doesn't have any buttons or snaps, but otherwise it's not bad for the price.  Though I wish it fit better, I'm glad I found this and can check off another Halloween costume!  Hopefully we can use it for a career day at some point as well haha!

title: Professional all weather dog hiker tested and approved!!
text: [[VIDEOID:618819090831e8f113552c18ce773ff0]] Yup, you read that right.  I am a professional dog hiker.  I take dogs off leash pack hiking on the foothill and mountain trails around the Salt Lake valley every morning, M-F for 3-5 miles (an hour and a half) in ANY weather (rain, snow, sleet, hail or blazing sun).  This poncho has become one of the things I can't live without in my dog van.  I have put it to the test in rain, sleet and snow and stayed nice and dry!  It's thick without feeling heavy.  I love the hood.  I love that you can make/adjust the "sleeves" with the snaps.  That is SUPER useful.  That way you can pop your hands out of small openings if you need to use them (which I do) but can easily pull your arms and and hands back inside for full coverage when needed.  I have a top of the line Mammut brand rain jacket that used to be the only thing I would use in wet conditions, however, I also wear a Camelbak backpack that isn't water proof.  It does come with a waterproof shell to protect most of the pack when needed, but I have to pull that out and put it on which can be a pain and it doesn't protect the entire bag.  Also, the jacket and rain shell do nothing for my legs.  In 5 seconds I can throw this poncho on over my body AND my backpack and have full dryness coverage from my head to about my shins.  I wear waterproof hiking boots and water resistant socks and pants on rainy days so that pretty much means completely dry!  I can't tell you what a difference it makes to be able to hike without having soggy undies!  I have also put this poncho to the test walking through scrub bushes and trees and have had ZERO tears or rips in the fabric.  5 stars very well earned!  Oh and I also love that it comes with a little zipper pouch to store it in when dry and that it actually CAN be folded up and put back in there easily after the first use haha.  RECOMMEND!

metadata.title: Women's Lightweight Stylish Rain Poncho Black

title: Puts all of our beanies to SHAME in warmth and comfort!
text: The material quality and comfort of this hat is TOP NOTCH!  I was hoping it would fit my head better but it's really quite large.  I'm a 37 y/o woman with a very average head and while it will stay on (especially with the flaps down and tied), it is NOT designed with my head size in mind.  My husband however has a much larger head and it fits him perfectly!  He's much more concerned about fashion over function than I am so I don't know if he'll be wearing it out other than for shoveling snow or maybe walking the dog very early in the morning, but truly it is PERFECT for that purpose during our long cold Salt Lake City winters!  It's supposed to be 9 degrees this week and it's not even November yet.  This is the warmest hat we have ever had in our house.  It puts every beanie we own to SHAME!  Another thing I love about this hat is that unlike most of my beanies which eventually give me ear fatigue (I have stick out ears that don't like being pinned to my head by hats or headphones) these ear flaps cause no ear fatigue whatsoever!!  I'll probably wear it for that reason alone, even if it is a little on the large side for my head.  Elmer Fudd would be proud!

title: My 7 y/o LOVES his "Dragon Feet"!
text: My 7 year old (we got the big kid 4/5) has a plush dragon that he adores and LOVES these slippers!  They're the first slippers he's ever had and he calls them his "Dragon feet".  They're probably supposed to be dinosaurs or monsters but to him they're dragon feet.  What is significant is that he as autism and is VERY particular about what he puts on his feet (or his body period for that matter)!  These slippers stay on (though are a little big) and best of all he finds them comfortable enough to keep on his feet for hours at a time while playing all over the house!  I never thought he'd voluntarily wear slippers, let alone love them, but he loves these!  The material on the soles could be a little more heavy duty to make them last longer, and the interior tag is obnoxious (had to cut them off).  Also, my son doesn't know what he's missing, but I wish they had chosen a softer, fleecier fabric for the interior but otherwise we're big fans of these over here!  I can definitely recommend for kids for fun.  Would make a very cute Christmas gift.  Just so you know either slipper can go on either foot.  There is no left or right, which makes it even easier for kids to put on themselves.

title: Quality materials/Runs too large in the waist and bust areas.
text: I have eight children. Eight. When people ask, “How do you do it?!” I reply, “I eat a lot of chocolate.” It’s true. Chocolate comes in so many delicious forms, each one designed to grant a few minutes of sanity-saving endorphin release, that it is my go-to coping mechanism. Unfortunately, both motherhood and nature’s stress reliever have blessed me with a few extra pounds around the middle and on my upper thighs. Enter the dreaded swimsuit season. The fashion industry has come up with two solutions to these problems; ruching to disguise slight fat rolls, and boy-cut bottoms to hide thigh girth. This swimsuit has both, and I was offered the opportunity to pick one up at a discount, in exchange for an honest review. I figured I have nothing to lose, so here we go, the pros: The swimsuit arrived neatly folded in a reusable plastic zippered bag. Save it, as it will come in handy for stashing a wet swimsuit into your gym bag or car. The seams are well-sewn and the fabric is sturdy and thick. It is comfortable and not binding. This swimsuit would be really flattering to my figure if it weren’t for the cons: First, it simply doesn’t fit me. I try to be realistic, so I ordered the size that I normally wear, as opposed to the size that I’d like to wear. It is too long in the waist. I am 5’8”, so I don’t have an especially short waist, but this swimsuit is way too long. I thought, okay, maybe it’s just a little extra ruching, and I pulled it up so that all of the extra fabric was at the waist. That’s when I really noticed the draft in my nether-regions. The fabric that is supposed to cover my girl parts is way too narrow (or the leg holes are way too wide) if pulled up, leaving me exposed on the sides of my crotch. I haven’t had a Brazilian, so imagine how attractive that must be, and it kind of negates the coverage on the upper thigh, anyway. Unfortunately, when I pulled it back down to once again cover my upper thighs, the fabric at the groin hung down about two inches. Finally, I am currently breastfeeding my youngest, so I have an ample bosom. I’m sporting D’s, yet I don’t even fill the (very nice quality sewn-in underwire) cups. I do wish that the built-in bra extended all the way around to the back for extra support for my “girls.” Tying them up using the straps at the neck just doesn’t win the battle against gravity. Perhaps all of these problems will be rectified if I exchange it for a smaller size. I'll give it a 3 star rating in the meantime. Disclaimer: Before making a purchase, I research a product thoroughly, and I depend on honest reviews to aid in my decision making. This product was received for free or at a discount in exchange for an honest and unbiased review. While I have shaken my head at some of the 5-star reviews I have seen other professional reviewers give to lousy 1-star products, simply because they received them for free, I do my best to keep my reviews thorough and unbiased. I won’t give a good rating to anything that I wouldn’t be willing to shell out my own hard-earned cash for. Feel free to ask any questions that you may have. If this review has been helpful for you, please indicate by hitting the “yes” button below.

title: One of The Most Disappointing Amazon Finds
text:
For the longest time, I have wanted a good pair of flare jeans. When I saw these, I thought that they were funky and cool. I thought they would be an excellent way to spice up any outfit. The material of the jeans is more like jeggings which is unfortunate because I was hoping the material would be like regular denim. However, they are stretchy, which can be a plus.

They are also very long. I am 5’6, and I would have to wear them with heels or boots so that the fabric is not dragging on the floor. They were loose on the legs but tight on the hips. I was hoping that these jeans would work because I have wanted them for a long time, but they just did not. I ended up giving these pants to my sister, who has a different body type than me, and they looked lovely on her.

Overall, I feel unsatisfied and upset with how these looked on me. The jeans were uncomfortable because they were tight on the hips and loose on the legs. They were also way too long, so they would only work if you have long legs or wear them with heels. I gave them to my sister, so I am happy they worked for someone, but I wanted them to work for me. I am incredibly displeased and unhappy with these jeans.

title: Good Jacket But Could be Better
text:
Since my gym class started this semester, I have needed a workout jacket, and I found this one. This jacket is good, but alas, it is not to my fullest expectations. I have organized my thoughts by category for your convenience.

THE FIT
The jacket fits me like a glove in the best way! I am 5'4, 125 pounds, have a 34-35" bust and a 27-28" waist; the medium was perfect. I ordered according to the size chart, and I recommend you do the same. It is accurate. However, I will note that the thumb holes are very uncomfortable. I feel like they are digging into my skin and pulling my thumbs; it is pretty unpleasant for long periods.

THE FEEL
I do not care for the feel as much as I do the fit. The jacket has a cheap swimsuit-like material, and I had higher expectations for $35. It is not uncomfortable, nor is it super comfortable. It is just meh. You can probably do better than this for less.

WORKOUT
I have yet to use this jacket in my class, but it is a sturdy jacket from the feel of it. I do not have any concerns in that regard. I will use it tomorrow and update the review if things change.

CONSENSUS
I probably would not recommend this jacket. It is on the pricier side for something that is, all in all, just average. It fits amazingly and is very flattering, but its overly apparent flaws overshadow that. I recommend you look elsewhere for a better jacket unless you desire a specific color.

title: Attractive crocodile design
text: This purse looks more expensive than what it costs and the black patent is very shiny, and the croc pattern is very attractive.  The purse itself is the perfect size at approximately 12” X 9”. It comes with a detachable should strap which make carrying this purse across your shoulder, especially during the winter months when having a bulky coat on makes it’s almost impossible to throw a purse over your shoulder. The strap itself is also adjustable to however long or short you would like it to be. The carrying handles are just about the perfect size for me but I keep the shoulder strap on at all times. The purse itself is pretty stiff as you would expect a patent item to be, but I can see that mine is starting to loosen the more that I use it. I love the added pockets on the inside and they are just perfect for my cell phone or other items of your choosing.  There are snaps on both ends of the purse to make it just a tad smaller, but I found that I like it better in the unsnapped position as it makes it easier to get to the items inside.  My purse did not have any smell to it as some of the other reviewers had noticed. What I like best about this purse is how nicely it stands up and does not flop and fall over.  I will be getting a lot of use out of this purse. I did received this item at a discount in exchange for an honest, unbiased review, and I am grateful for that opportunity.

title: Love this little wallet!
text: The LifeTek front pocket leather wallet was exactly what I was looking for. Although this item says it’s for men, I bought in anyway because of the design. I wanted an item like this that would hold  a few credit cards, drivers license and a little bit of cash. I also wanted to be able to put this in my front pocket without a lot of bulk. This wallet certainly filled all those desires. The wallet only measures 4” x 2 ¾” and is very thin. The high grade quality leather used in the manufacturing design is very evident as it is soft and luxurious. With a slot to put your driver’s license that has a see through plastic cover, allows you to show your license without having to remove it from the wallet. I really like that feature as the fewer times you have to remove cards, the less wear and tear you will have on your wallet. With two card slots on the back, each slot will hold three cards each, although I only have a total of three cards in order to keep my wallet very slim. The wallet opens slightly across the top and one side so that if you wanted to slide a bill or two inside, you can do that as well.  When I have this inside my front pocket I can’t even tell it is there, and you really can’t see that it adds any bulk to the look of my pants. The only thing I may have a problem with is forgetting that it is inside my pants pocket. I would hate to run this through the washer as I really like this little wallet. I don’t think either a man or woman can go wrong with this leather wallet. This does come in a nice gift box ready for wrapping.  I did receive a discount on this item for an honest, unbiased review. I can guarantee that this review is honest as I really love this item.

title: Very nice, but runs small
text: I was really excited to be getting this shirt as I had been looking for something like this for a long time. Denim is typically so heavy, that I didn’t really want a heavy denim shirt. When I saw this one advertised as light weight, I thought I would take the chance. This shirt did almost two weeks to arrive, but I don’t know if it is manufactured in China but it does say it is imported. The shirt does say that it was designed in the USA, but I could not find on the tag where it was made. The shirt is a light blue color, and is long sleeve with tabs that allow you to button up the sleeve which I really appreciate. The sizing however is off as mine is marked as a 2XL but fits more like a 1XL. I would say to definitely order up a size especially for a plus size woman. The sleeve’s are also just a “little” tight, but not enough to make it uncomfortable. The length is pretty long and on me since I am only 5’2”, it looks best on me when worn as a layering top.  This shirt is well made and the buttons seems to be sewn on securely. The shirt is made from 100% cotton, so I would recommend not putting this in the dryer. All in all, I am pretty happy with my shirt and I look forward to getting a lot of wear out of it. I would have given this a 5 star had the sizing not be off. I did receive this item at a discount in return for an honest, unbiased review.

This was a cute dress, just not for me. I think it would look great on a really tall person. At 5'4" in height and "on the slightly thinner side of average"

Also, the green color was not a vibrant as I had hoped. Sizing runs a bit small, imho, so size up unless you really like a club fit. Otherwise, it's well made and very reasonably priced. I love this brand and will buy from them again. Sorry I have to return this style, but I will shop for something else in their collection to replace it.

title: Nice pattern; looks good on larger figures
text: I got the dress in beige plaid. Everyone said it looked like Burberry print. Yes, the plaid does not match up, but because of the cut and style of the dress, it appears as if that is part of the design, so it works. The fabric is thin. Depending on the conditions of the room and the color of your dress, you might need a slip. The dress was easy to slip on.  The belt it comes with is just a simple sash in the same pattern. It really need to be an inch wider so it covers the waist seam. I replaced it with a black suede sash belt that matched my boots, and it looked great. The look on my body, however, wasn’t so great. I’m average shape and size. It did my figure no favors. I personally think it best flatters figures a little bigger than average. It served its purpose for the day and I got compliments on the pattern, but I will probably give this away to a charity or a friend who will look great in it.

title: Love the color and the size
text:
This wallet is so great. I needed a small wallet for a ridiculously tiny purse. I found this after a bit of searching and then wondered what took me so long. I have another one of these in a smooth lighter pink leather that I carry my government ID in for work. I use this every day. I have a larger wallet in my pocket book to carry my less frequently used cards. This one is small enough to put in a pants pocket so a woman doesn't have to take her purse with her. I love the bright pink color. The pebbled leather feels quality and having had another leather wallet by this company for a while I feel certain it will hold up and look good for a long time.

I don't keep much in it. Two cards per slot fits, but makes it feel thick. Also, while the center pouch is zippered, I prefer to not carry change in it. It makes it fat quickly. I like to carry a small amount of folding money, a few credit cards, frequent diner cards, my driver's license and that is about it. It would hold more, but I think it's thinness is it's best quality.

title: Three Way Convertible Bag with Canvas and Leather Retro Look
text:
I like the FRESION BAGS CO. MESSENGER BRIEFCASE BAG as it can be used as Backpack, Briefcase or Shoulder Bag. When used as Briefcase both Shoulder and Backpack Straps are hidden away in enclosed compartments.

The FRESION Messenger Bag is lightweight. Construction is of retro looking Grey/Brown canvas with leather straps, zipper pulls, handles and accent. There are nine (9) zippered pockets showing on the outside of the bag and one inside. I like that all the little compartments have zippers which keeps smaller items from falling out. The largest compartment will house a computer and there is three inches of space for business meetings materials. The internal zipper section is here also. The computer space is padded with an elastic security strap over the top. The other large compartment is good for quickly needed files, calculator, pens and pencils.

Even when almost empty the case will stand on its own. This facilitates putting items into the bag, finding things and removing used documents. The Backpack Straps have their own zippered compartment. They are totally out of the way when not in use. The same is true for the shoulder strap which fits into a slotted compartment on the cover material of the backpack straps. There is a slotted compartment on the other side of the bag. When the bag is used in shoulder or backpack mode the carry straps fold away into these same two compartments and secured with magnetic snap. There are two “D” rigs on one end of the bag. All of the interior is lined in a satin type material.

Recommended Five ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Star

title: Outdoor Umbrella Feels sturdy…subdued red Chili color… single crank raises/lowers/tilts
text:
The TEMPERA (ASIN- B09NW1VKH6) CHILI 🌶 COLOR TILT OUTDOOR UMBRELLA arrives assembled and ready to use. The bottom post section of the ten foot (10’) tall umbrella slides into a weighted base ( not provided ). The top section of Umbrella and crank assembly slides into the bottom post locking in place with push-button spring loaded detent. As I have an existing post in place I tested compatibility finding the top half of the Tempera Umbrella works fine with my post. However, we are using the manufacturer post as provided.

The crank requires 14 revolutions (360 degree turns) to raise or lower the awning. After awning is raised, continuous crank will tilt the top to user desired location. As it is cloudy day we only tested tilt a few degrees and returned it to straight position.

The Chili 🌶 color is NOT bright. In our opinion it is subdued and pleasing to our eyes. There is no stripe in the material. There are black speckles along with darkened red background. We like it! It adds color but not overpowering.

The umbrella kit includes the top half which is the Umbrella and all controls, the bottom post to fit into weighted base and User Instruction Pamphlet. Permanently attached to the material is a two inch (2”) strap of the same material, with Hook and Loop fasteners, to secure around the awning.
Recommended Five ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Star

title: Nice material - Production quality marginal
text:
YRW MEN'S LONG SLEEVE SHIRT is open collar. The Review Shirt is NOT button down style.

At first glance the shirt has nice material, bright color and attractive in my observation. When looking at detail of manufacturing I found quality moderate to poor. The pattern of the wide strips do not match on front, back or at cuff area. The most distracting to me is the misalignment of pocket on front of shirt. The Review Shirt has hanging threads throughout, double stitching at many places, short/long stitches in same run plus not straight. I liked the material and Steam iron on cotton setting removed wrinkles.

My opinion of use is as cover for Beach or Poolside. Fit of the XX-large shirt seems on small side of that range. I normally wear large or extra large and experience this shirt slightly larger. The product site DOES show a shirt with mis-matched pattern of the pocket on the shirt and shirt arrived as shown… mis-matched.
Three ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Star

title: Lightweight talking Watch connects with APP and Bluetooth
text:
[[VIDEOID:7ace2370399902867ebce2d61f0e8ae3]] FIVE SENSES ATOMIC WATCH 3rd generation talking watch is supplied with User Setup Instructions Manual, extra battery with tool to replace battery. The band is expansion style and is aluminum look matching the case which appear to be aluminum.

The watch arrives charged but not activated. Press of top side button activates watch. Once activated there is NO, OFF switch. Setup requires download of Android or IOS APP. Bluetooth on cell = ON. The APP requires NAME and EMAIL address. Attempt to avoid providing this information, stops setup. It also causes APP confusion.

Backward to restart setup ….. Insert name-email. Next screen requires pressing lower right button. Instructions State … “ Press/Release” - that step, will NOT work. Press until TONE IS HEARD - then Pairing will commence. This was no issue. We were in 8:xx AM time zone and watch in 9:xx AM setting. It proceeded to wind through all of the hours until it returned to “7:xxAM time” No…this is not an error. Time shown on face of Watch is ONE HOUR BEHIND ACTUAL TIME - INCORRECT! VOICE PROMPT does state CORRECT time. Time SHOWN in APP is CORRECT time. WATCH is not usable showing time one hour behind actual time!

Cleared APP … Reloaded APP… Same result. Except this time I had to go through several screens to prove I was not a BOT.

LAST ATTEMPT….. RESET Watch by holding lower button over ten seconds until hearing beep. ( Twice )
Erased and Reloaded APP …. Completed Setup procedure with no issue.
RESULT…. Watch Face Time = One Hour behind actual time
Voice Prompt states correct time ….. Time shown on APP FACE is Correct Time

Manufacturer has used EMAIL INFORMATION to send direct communication to user before this review has been published by Amazon. NOT Recommended…. One ⭐️ Star

Your time looking at my Review is appreciated. The intent is you found it Valuable, Informative, Useful and HELPFUL. 😃
